WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:00.099
Provided by explosiveskull
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull

00:00.101 --> 00:02.434
<i>We come
to you now with revelations</i>

00:02.567 --> 00:04.067
<i>about last week's attack
in London.</i>

00:04.201 --> 00:06.533
<i>An anonymous source
provided this video.</i>

00:06.667 --> 00:09.234
<i>It shows Quentin Beck,
aka Mysterio,</i>

00:09.368 --> 00:11.101
<i>moments before his death.</i>

00:11.234 --> 00:13.434
<i>You may find
this video disturbing.</i>

00:13.567 --> 00:15.667
<i>I managed to
send the Elemental back,</i>

00:15.800 --> 00:17.934
<i>but I don't think I'm gonna
make it off this bridge.</i>

00:18.067 --> 00:19.600
<i>Spider-Man attacked me.</i>

00:19.734 --> 00:21.967
<i>He has an army of drones,
Stark technology.</i>

00:22.101 --> 00:25.567
<i>He's saying he's gonna be
the new Iron Man. No one else.</i>

00:25.700 --> 00:27.900
<i>Are you sure you want
to commence the drone attack?</i>

00:28.034 --> 00:29.867
<i>There will be
significant casualties.</i>

00:30.001 --> 00:31.867
<i>Do it. Execute them all.</i>

00:36.167 --> 00:39.234
<i>This shocking video
was released earlier today</i>

00:39.368 --> 00:42.267
<i>on the controversial
news website TheDailyBugle.net.</i>

00:42.401 --> 00:44.267
<i>There you have it, folks.
Conclusive proof</i>

00:44.401 --> 00:46.401
<i>that Spider-Man was responsible</i>

00:46.533 --> 00:48.667
<i>for the brutal murder
of Mysterio,</i>

00:48.800 --> 00:50.234
<i>an interdimensional warrior</i>

00:50.368 --> 00:52.134
<i>who gave his life
to protect our planet</i>

00:52.267 --> 00:54.633
<i>and who will, no doubt,
go down in history</i>

00:54.767 --> 00:58.434
<i>as the greatest superhero
of all time.</i>

00:58.567 --> 00:59.934
<i>But that's not all, folks.</i>

01:00.067 --> 01:01.600
<i>Here's the real blockbuster.</i>

01:01.734 --> 01:03.734
<i>Brace yourselves.
You might wanna sit down.</i>

01:03.867 --> 01:07.067
<i>Spider-Man's real...
Spider-Man's real name is...</i>

01:07.201 --> 01:10.967
<i>Spider-Man's name
is Peter Parker.</i>

01:12.067 --> 01:13.567
What the f...?

01:13.700 --> 01:16.134
<i>That's right, folks.
Peter Parker.</i>

01:16.267 --> 01:19.001
<i>A 17-year-old
high school delinquent...</i>

01:19.134 --> 01:21.800
- She knows him.
- Are you Spider-Man's girlfriend?

01:21.934 --> 01:22.800
<i>...is, in fact...</i>

01:22.934 --> 01:24.500
Are you Spider-Man's
girlfriend?

01:24.633 --> 01:26.567
<i>...the vile vigilante villain
Spider-Man.</i>

01:26.700 --> 01:28.700
- Yo, it's him.
- Uh, whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:28.834 --> 01:30.867
- Please don't touch her, sir.
- You're just a kid?

01:31.001 --> 01:32.567
- You murdered Mysterio?
- Um...

01:32.700 --> 01:34.067
- You helped him?
- No, I didn't...

01:34.201 --> 01:36.234
Come on, kid,
let me see your face.

01:36.368 --> 01:37.700
He hit me.
Spider-Man hit me!

01:37.834 --> 01:39.368
- Come on.
- He hit me.

01:39.500 --> 01:41.368
<i>All this time,
people looked up to this boy</i>

01:41.500 --> 01:43.201
<i>and called him a hero.</i>

01:43.334 --> 01:46.633
<i>I'll tell you what I call him,
public enemy number one!</i>

01:46.767 --> 01:49.468
I told you I never wanted
to do this ever again!

01:49.600 --> 01:51.401
MJ, I'm so sorry,
but I can't see anything

01:51.533 --> 01:52.600
with your hand in my...

01:52.734 --> 01:54.001
Sorry. Where are we
gonna go?

01:54.134 --> 01:55.900
- I don't know. Your house?
- No! No!

01:56.034 --> 01:57.500
My dad will kill you.

01:57.633 --> 01:59.401
What? You said
your dad really liked me.

01:59.533 --> 02:01.301
Yeah, well, not anymore.

02:03.834 --> 02:06.067
<i>Dude!</i>

02:06.201 --> 02:07.134
Dude!

02:07.267 --> 02:08.401
<i>Dude!</i>

02:08.533 --> 02:09.468
Dude!

02:11.034 --> 02:12.267
I'm so sorry.
Are you okay?

02:12.401 --> 02:13.700
No, not really. Uh...

02:13.834 --> 02:15.267
Yo, Peter!

02:22.900 --> 02:24.500
We should go.
We should go. Come on.

02:24.633 --> 02:27.067
- You said you don't want to swing.
- Swing me.

02:27.201 --> 02:28.800
Okay. We can take the subway.

02:32.434 --> 02:33.468
No.

02:39.434 --> 02:40.468
Look out!

02:49.101 --> 02:50.468
That was so much worse.

02:50.600 --> 02:51.667
Okay. It's okay.

02:51.800 --> 02:54.734
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:54.867 --> 02:57.800
Come on, come on, come on.
Okay, I'm so sorry.

03:07.533 --> 03:10.368
Okay. Okay.

03:10.500 --> 03:11.533
I'm sorry.

03:13.567 --> 03:16.267
I just feel so dumb. I didn't
realize you were miserable.

03:16.401 --> 03:18.067
No, it was really fun, right?

03:18.201 --> 03:19.734
That's why they call it
a fling.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.301
- And we flung.
- It was fun.

03:21.434 --> 03:22.800
I could've been more fun.

03:22.934 --> 03:24.267
- I can be fun.
- We'll hang out again.

03:24.401 --> 03:26.434
Like, when do you think?

03:28.934 --> 03:30.067
I should see what that is.

03:30.201 --> 03:32.067
- No, no, no.
- It's what I do.

03:32.201 --> 03:34.201
- He's always coming and going.
- Peter?

03:34.334 --> 03:36.767
Oh, no.

03:36.900 --> 03:39.267
- I don't know what to do.
- Peter. Peter.

03:39.401 --> 03:41.368
- Oh, I...
- I didn't see anything.

03:41.500 --> 03:42.734
This isn't what
it looks like.

03:42.867 --> 03:44.533
- No, no, May.
- Practice safe...

03:44.667 --> 03:47.368
Oh, hey. You must be MJ!

03:47.500 --> 03:49.967
- Yeah. Nice to meet you.
- So nice to meet you.

03:50.101 --> 03:51.934
Wait, have you
been crying?

03:52.067 --> 03:53.167
We broke up.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.567
- Hey, Spider-Man!
- Oh. Oh, uh...

03:57.800 --> 03:59.434
Thank you. I didn't know
you broke up.

03:59.567 --> 04:00.834
I thought you were
in love, May.

04:00.967 --> 04:02.468
Can we talk about this
in the kitchen?

04:02.600 --> 04:04.101
I should probably leave.

04:04.234 --> 04:06.134
I thought you guys
were such a handsome couple.

04:06.267 --> 04:08.301
It's really about boundaries.

04:08.434 --> 04:10.700
- Let me answer the door.
- Let's go here.

04:10.834 --> 04:12.267
- Is that the door?
- Hey. Is it true?

04:12.401 --> 04:14.301
- I was gonna go, but...
- Not now.

04:14.434 --> 04:17.368
I didn't know you were
so awkward about sex, Peter.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.434
This has nothing to do
with sex.

04:19.567 --> 04:22.900
If you wanna go over it again.
I mean... What's that sound?

04:24.234 --> 04:26.633
- Hey, Spider-Man!
- Oh, my God.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.667
I mean, I'm happy to rehash it
if you want to.

04:29.800 --> 04:32.401
You take care of your
side, I'll take care of mine.

04:34.867 --> 04:36.267
What is up
with this phone?

04:36.401 --> 04:38.267
Will you get off your phones
for five minutes?

04:38.401 --> 04:40.633
I just wanna talk to you
about your relationship, okay?

04:40.767 --> 04:41.734
Peter?

04:44.834 --> 04:45.767
What?

04:47.500 --> 04:49.800
- Is that...?
- Is that here?

04:49.934 --> 04:51.334
Um...

05:04.101 --> 05:06.368
- Yo, Peter Parker!
- Yo, Peter!

05:06.500 --> 05:08.401
Maybe it's not
such a big deal.

05:08.533 --> 05:10.700
<i>Spider-Menace!</i>

05:10.834 --> 05:12.867
<i>Governments around the world
launch investigations</i>

05:13.001 --> 05:15.267
<i>into the murderer
known as Spider-Man,</i>

05:15.401 --> 05:17.034
<i>aka Peter Parker,</i>

05:17.167 --> 05:19.967
<i>aka the web-headed
war criminal</i>

05:20.101 --> 05:22.334
who, for years,
has been terrorizing

05:22.468 --> 05:24.434
the decent citizens
of New York.

05:24.567 --> 05:26.434
<i>Well, now this city
and the world</i>

05:26.567 --> 05:28.301
<i>see him for what he truly is.</i>

05:28.434 --> 05:30.334
<i>Murderer! Mysterio forever!</i>

05:30.468 --> 05:32.067
<i>New details from last week's</i>

05:32.201 --> 05:34.500
<i>devastating attack in London
have emerged.</i>

05:34.633 --> 05:37.468
<i>For more, we go now to Joint
Intelligence headquarters.</i>

05:37.600 --> 05:40.101
<i>Authorities
just a short while ago confirmed</i>

05:40.234 --> 05:42.434
<i>that the deadly drones used
in the London attack</i>

05:42.567 --> 05:44.800
<i>were designed
by Stark Industries.</i>

05:44.934 --> 05:46.934
Federal agents! Open up!

05:47.067 --> 05:49.434
Federal agents? You stay here.

05:49.567 --> 05:50.967
Department of Damage Control.

05:51.101 --> 05:52.900
We have a warrant
for the arrest of Peter Parker.

05:53.034 --> 05:54.567
- You know the Fourth Amendment?
- Sure.

05:54.700 --> 05:56.134
Unreasonable search
and seizure?

05:56.267 --> 05:58.767
Get in here, guys. Let's go.

05:58.900 --> 06:01.001
I didn't kill Quentin Beck.
The drones did, okay?

06:01.134 --> 06:02.934
- The drones that are yours.
- No.

06:03.067 --> 06:05.301
Well, look. Nick Fury was there
the entire time.

06:05.434 --> 06:07.234
Ask him.
He can explain everything.

06:07.368 --> 06:10.101
Nick Fury has been off-planet
for the last year.

06:10.234 --> 06:12.434
- What?
- Peter! Hey.

06:12.567 --> 06:15.101
MJ! They have nothing
to do with this, sir.

06:15.234 --> 06:17.767
Don't say anything
without a lawyer.

06:17.900 --> 06:19.600
I want a lawyer.

06:19.734 --> 06:22.567
- Ms. Jones-Watson.
- Jones. I don't go by Watson.

06:22.700 --> 06:24.967
Ms. Jones, why do you
want a lawyer if...?

06:25.101 --> 06:26.301
If I have nothing to hide?

06:26.434 --> 06:27.800
Exactly. Unless...

06:27.934 --> 06:29.734
- I'm actually guilty of something?
- Mm-hm.

06:29.867 --> 06:32.401
I'm very aware of your tactics
and my rights.

06:32.533 --> 06:34.334
Just answer my questions.

06:34.468 --> 06:36.134
I've seen your file.

06:36.267 --> 06:37.468
You're a smart young woman

06:37.600 --> 06:39.633
with a bright future
ahead of her.

06:39.767 --> 06:41.267
Why would you risk it all

06:41.401 --> 06:44.533
by getting involved with
a vigilante like Peter Parker?

06:45.533 --> 06:47.633
So sorry to keep you waiting.

06:47.767 --> 06:49.267
- Can we get Ned a snack?
- Absolutely.

06:49.401 --> 06:50.734
- He's been waiting.
- I got you.

06:50.867 --> 06:52.934
Dude, I'm so sorry about that.

06:53.067 --> 06:55.134
I'm not supposed
to say anything to you.

06:55.267 --> 06:57.267
Not even a thing.
I just have one question.

06:57.401 --> 06:59.667
When MJ told you
Peter was Spider-Man...

06:59.800 --> 07:01.500
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. Heh.
- What's up?

07:01.633 --> 07:03.001
I-I knew way before MJ did.

07:03.134 --> 07:04.468
I was Spider-Man's
"guy in the chair."

07:04.600 --> 07:05.800
I know about those.

07:05.934 --> 07:07.600
Dude, half my guys
are guys in the chair.

07:07.734 --> 07:09.001
Exactly. You would know.

07:09.134 --> 07:11.368
I literally helped him
find the Vulture.

07:11.500 --> 07:13.767
- I didn't know that.
- I helped him hack a suit once

07:13.900 --> 07:15.301
and helped him get to space.

07:15.434 --> 07:17.800
So in Spider-Man's
illegal vigilantism,

07:17.934 --> 07:19.934
you were his main accomplice.

07:22.867 --> 07:25.567
I would like to have my words
stricken from the record.

07:25.700 --> 07:29.201
With all due respect, and
I mean that very insincerely,

07:29.334 --> 07:32.334
unless you have some real
specific charges to throw at us,

07:32.468 --> 07:35.101
legally, you can't hold us here.

07:35.234 --> 07:37.567
- You should definitely lawyer up.
- Excuse me?

07:37.700 --> 07:39.767
Child endangerment's
a nasty rap.

07:39.900 --> 07:41.633
A boy was entrusted to you,

07:41.767 --> 07:44.101
and as his legal guardian,
essentially his mother,

07:44.234 --> 07:46.368
you not only allowed him
to endanger himself,

07:46.500 --> 07:48.134
but you actually
encouraged it.

07:48.267 --> 07:49.900
Who does that?

07:50.034 --> 07:51.967
I wanna see Peter right now.

08:22.101 --> 08:24.800
<i>Stark
Industries was caught in the web</i>

08:24.934 --> 08:27.468
<i>of the Spider-Man-Mysterio
controversy today,</i>

08:27.600 --> 08:30.067
<i>when federal agents
opened an investigation</i>

08:30.201 --> 08:32.900
<i>into missing Stark technology.</i>

08:33.034 --> 08:35.468
<i>Agents wanna know
exactly what was taken...</i>

08:35.600 --> 08:37.267
At least they used
a good picture.

08:37.401 --> 08:39.167
What is happening?

08:41.067 --> 08:43.867
That's great. Thank you.

08:44.001 --> 08:45.567
Well, I have
some good news, Peter.

08:45.700 --> 08:47.067
I don't believe
any of the charges

08:47.201 --> 08:49.034
- against you are gonna stick.
- Wait, seriously?

08:49.167 --> 08:50.700
- I knew it.
- Nice.

08:50.834 --> 08:52.368
My God, Mr. Murdock, thank you.

08:52.500 --> 08:54.134
- Thank you, Matt.
- That's amazing.

08:54.267 --> 08:55.301
- You're welcome.
- Perfect.

08:55.434 --> 08:57.468
- However, Mr. Hogan.
- Yes?

08:57.600 --> 09:00.767
The feds are investigating
that missing technology.

09:00.900 --> 09:03.167
I understand your loyalty
to Mr. Stark and his legacy,

09:03.301 --> 09:04.633
but if you were involved...

09:04.767 --> 09:06.500
- If I was?
- I advise securing a lawyer.

09:06.633 --> 09:09.468
I need a lawyer because I'm...?
I thought he was...

09:09.600 --> 09:10.900
You said there's no charge.

09:11.034 --> 09:12.834
I could say
under advisement of counsel,

09:12.967 --> 09:15.001
I refuse to answer
the question respectfully

09:15.134 --> 09:17.101
because the answer
can incriminate me...

09:17.234 --> 09:19.600
It's in <i>Goodfellas.</i> What's the
thing they say in <i>Goodfellas?</i>

09:19.734 --> 09:21.401
I know that's what you think.
Calm down.

09:21.533 --> 09:22.934
Let's hear what
he has to say. Matt?

09:23.067 --> 09:25.667
You're gonna need
a really good lawyer.

09:25.800 --> 09:27.767
You may have dodged
your legal troubles

09:27.900 --> 09:29.334
but things will get much worse.

09:29.468 --> 09:31.800
There is still
the court of public opinion.

09:34.034 --> 09:36.434
Murderer! Mysterio forever!

09:38.867 --> 09:40.267
How did you just do that?

09:40.401 --> 09:42.201
I'm a really good lawyer.

09:44.533 --> 09:46.633
We're gonna need
a safer place to live.

09:57.368 --> 09:59.034
Oh. Ah.

09:59.167 --> 10:00.934
How do we...?
How do we...?

10:01.067 --> 10:02.967
<i>Alarm system deactivated.</i>

10:05.700 --> 10:08.500
It looks nice.
And this is safe.

10:11.734 --> 10:14.967
Welcome to the spiritual oasis.

10:15.101 --> 10:16.500
You like <i>Donkey Kong Jr.?</i>

10:18.700 --> 10:20.834
<i>Nicky from Jersey
City, you're on the line.</i>

10:20.967 --> 10:23.600
<i>I'm not saying I don't
want to honor the Avengers,</i>

10:23.734 --> 10:25.967
<i>but, you know,
not doing it this way.</i>

10:26.101 --> 10:27.633
<i>Putting the
Captain America shield</i>

10:27.767 --> 10:29.468
<i>on the Statue of Liberty?</i>

10:29.600 --> 10:31.301
<i>Nah, that will look ridiculous.</i>

10:31.434 --> 10:33.401
<i>Leave the Statue
of Liberty alone.</i>

10:33.533 --> 10:35.567
Oh, Happy.

10:35.700 --> 10:37.700
<i>Did you send in
your applications yet?</i>

10:37.834 --> 10:39.301
I just finished my MIT one.

10:39.434 --> 10:40.700
- <i>You?</i>
- Same.

10:40.834 --> 10:43.101
Can you imagine if
we both got in? And Ned?

10:43.234 --> 10:44.734
Yeah, but we'd have
to get scholarships

10:44.867 --> 10:46.267
so we could actually go.

10:46.401 --> 10:48.600
You got the scores
and the grades.

10:48.734 --> 10:50.134
<i>You think I'm being
too pragmatic.</i>

10:50.267 --> 10:52.401
<i>No, no, no. Well...</i>

10:52.533 --> 10:53.767
<i>Kind of. It's okay.</i>

10:53.900 --> 10:55.434
It's one of my favorite
things about you.

10:55.567 --> 10:56.800
- Really?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

10:56.934 --> 10:58.767
What are your other
favorite things?

10:58.900 --> 11:00.600
I love your
relentless optimism.

11:00.734 --> 11:02.767
I am a glass-half-full
kind of gal.

11:02.900 --> 11:04.767
I really like how
you're a people person.

11:04.900 --> 11:07.167
I love people.
I love them so much.

11:07.301 --> 11:08.234
You like sports.

11:08.368 --> 11:09.600
<i>I think the Mets are gonna</i>

11:09.734 --> 11:11.234
- <i>go all the way this year.</i>
- <i>Really?</i>

11:11.368 --> 11:12.800
What's that noise?

11:12.934 --> 11:15.567
<i>Oh. It's Happy. Look.</i>

11:15.700 --> 11:18.567
<i>Gave his room to May
so he's sleeping down here.</i>

11:22.368 --> 11:25.600
I have a weird question. Um...

11:25.734 --> 11:28.401
Does any part of you
feel relieved about all of this?

11:31.767 --> 11:35.401
Ever since I got bit
by that spider...

11:35.533 --> 11:39.767
I've only had one week
where my life has felt normal.

11:39.900 --> 11:42.134
Or kind of normal, I guess.

11:42.267 --> 11:43.301
And...

11:44.600 --> 11:46.101
that was when
you found out.

11:46.234 --> 11:48.867
<i>Because then everyone
that was in my life</i>

11:49.001 --> 11:50.800
<i>that I wanted to know, knew.</i>

11:50.934 --> 11:51.934
<i>And it was perfect.</i>

11:52.067 --> 11:54.434
But now everybody knows and...

11:56.101 --> 11:59.401
I am the most famous person
in the entire world.

12:00.334 --> 12:02.101
And I'm still broke.

12:06.101 --> 12:07.667
I'm...

12:07.800 --> 12:10.001
excited to see you tomorrow.

12:11.934 --> 12:13.267
<i>Yeah. Me too.</i>

12:13.401 --> 12:14.800
Wrap it up.

12:14.934 --> 12:16.767
You both like each other.
We get it. Hang up.

12:16.900 --> 12:19.301
There's no new ground being
broken. I need my eight hours.

12:19.434 --> 12:21.001
Have you been listening
this whole time?

12:21.134 --> 12:23.001
- <i>Hi, Happy.</i>
- Not by choice.

12:23.134 --> 12:25.301
- MJ says hi.
- Hello.

12:25.434 --> 12:27.900
<i>We're covering
the first day of senior year</i>

12:28.034 --> 12:30.134
<i>for Midtown High's
most famous student,</i>

12:30.267 --> 12:31.600
<i>Peter Parker.</i>

12:31.734 --> 12:33.334
<i>Go get them, tiger.</i>

12:33.468 --> 12:35.500
<i>Or should I say "spider"?</i>

12:35.633 --> 12:38.767
<i>The crowd has continued
to grow here all morning long</i>

12:38.900 --> 12:40.867
<i>at the Midtown School
of Science...</i>

12:41.001 --> 12:42.800
<i>The crowd seems evenly divided</i>

12:42.934 --> 12:44.900
<i>between supporters
of Spider-Man</i>

12:45.034 --> 12:46.201
<i>and protestors.</i>

12:46.334 --> 12:50.101
MJ! MJ! MJ! We love you!

12:50.234 --> 12:52.600
MJ, are you gonna have
his spider-babies?

12:52.734 --> 12:55.633
Back up. Back up. Back up!

12:55.767 --> 12:57.967
MJ, you know
he's a murderer, right?

12:58.101 --> 12:59.633
Peter. Do a TikTok with me.

12:59.767 --> 13:02.900
- Mysterio forever!
- Do a flip!

13:03.034 --> 13:05.600
- Hey, let's see you and MJ kiss!
- Back off.

13:05.734 --> 13:06.934
Who are you?

13:07.067 --> 13:08.667
Ned Leeds.
Spider-Man's best friend.

13:08.800 --> 13:10.267
I'm Peter Parker's
best friend.

13:10.401 --> 13:12.267
You come at my boy,
you come at Flash Thompson.

13:12.401 --> 13:14.401
If you wanna read
about our inspiring friendship,

13:14.533 --> 13:16.567
you can in my new book,
<i>Flashpoint.</i>

13:16.700 --> 13:19.334
One spider, two hearts,
a million crazy-ass memories.

13:19.468 --> 13:20.800
Check it out.

13:23.434 --> 13:24.967
- Go.
- No, I gotta wait...

13:25.101 --> 13:25.967
No. Go.

13:26.101 --> 13:27.600
I'll see you inside, okay?

13:29.101 --> 13:31.167
<i>Keep watching</i> Midtown News
<i>all year</i>

13:31.301 --> 13:33.301
<i>as we bring you up close
and personal coverage</i>

13:33.434 --> 13:36.434
<i>of Peter fighting
his biggest battle yet,</i>

13:36.567 --> 13:38.234
<i>college admissions.</i>

13:42.167 --> 13:47.468
Peter, we would love to welcome
you back to Midtown High,

13:47.600 --> 13:49.434
where we shape heroes.

13:49.567 --> 13:51.368
Yeah, uh-huh. Or murderers.

13:51.500 --> 13:52.600
Stop it.

13:52.734 --> 13:55.101
It's an honor
to serve you, sir.

13:55.234 --> 13:56.201
It's not.

13:56.334 --> 13:57.600
Mysterio was right.

13:57.734 --> 13:59.434
- Stop. That's all.
- Mysterio was right.

13:59.567 --> 14:02.201
Some of the students
put this together for you.

14:02.334 --> 14:04.967
- No, you did that.
- I helped a little bit.

14:05.101 --> 14:07.967
I tried to stop you so
many times but you powered through.

14:08.101 --> 14:09.934
- He did all of that.
- Did a great job.

14:10.067 --> 14:12.001
I hope you have time
to check it out.

14:12.134 --> 14:14.800
Feel free to walk
or swing through the hallway.

14:14.934 --> 14:17.401
Or crawl on the ceiling
to avoid everybody.

14:17.533 --> 14:19.633
- We all know you can do it.
- I'm just gonna...

14:19.767 --> 14:20.834
I know what you did.

14:20.967 --> 14:22.101
Stop. You're
embarrassing yourself.

14:22.234 --> 14:23.734
He's a conspiracy
theorist.

14:37.867 --> 14:39.800
Can we just stay up here
all day?

14:39.934 --> 14:42.368
- It is so crazy down there.
- This one's good.

14:42.500 --> 14:44.234
"Some suggest
that Parker's powers

14:44.368 --> 14:47.468
include the male spider's
ability to hypnotize females,

14:47.600 --> 14:50.401
which he used to seduce
Jones-Watson

14:50.533 --> 14:53.101
- into his cult of personality."
- Oh, come on. Stop. Stop.

14:53.234 --> 14:55.533
Yes, my Spider-Lord.

15:03.401 --> 15:05.567
Finally some privacy.

15:05.700 --> 15:08.201
It is so crazy down there.

15:08.334 --> 15:10.434
So I was thinking...

15:10.567 --> 15:13.834
when we get into MIT,
we should live together.

15:13.967 --> 15:16.567
- Yeah, for sure.
- Yeah, I'd love that.

15:17.900 --> 15:19.633
- This is gonna be us.
- Yes.

15:19.767 --> 15:21.468
Minus the Frisbee
and the smiling.

15:21.600 --> 15:23.401
MIT's obviously the dream,

15:23.533 --> 15:25.401
but if we match up
our backup schools,

15:25.533 --> 15:27.667
then either way,
we'll be in Boston.

15:27.800 --> 15:29.767
New school, new town.
I can Spider-Man there.

15:29.900 --> 15:32.001
- They have crime in Boston, right?
- Yes.

15:32.134 --> 15:34.800
- Wicked crime.
- It'll be like a fresh start.

15:36.468 --> 15:38.267
What's up?

15:38.401 --> 15:41.001
I don't know. I just feel
like, if you don't...

15:41.134 --> 15:42.967
If you expect disappointment,

15:43.101 --> 15:45.301
then you can never really
get disappointed.

15:45.434 --> 15:46.867
Come on.

15:48.434 --> 15:51.267
Be a fresh start.
And we'll all be together.

15:52.734 --> 15:55.034
Yeah. No, you're right.
Fresh start.

15:55.167 --> 15:56.201
Yeah.

15:58.934 --> 16:00.434
Fresh start.

16:02.700 --> 16:04.034
First one's here!

16:08.533 --> 16:10.368
It's okay.
It's a backup school.

16:11.667 --> 16:12.700
Peter!

16:14.900 --> 16:15.934
No?

16:18.567 --> 16:19.567
Last one.

16:21.267 --> 16:22.301
MIT?

16:26.234 --> 16:27.967
Uh... Okay.

16:39.267 --> 16:40.900
Okay.

16:41.034 --> 16:42.468
- Phew.
- Ready?

16:42.600 --> 16:45.734
Jones. I told you to take down
the Halloween decorations.

16:45.867 --> 16:47.468
Actually, that was Sasha so...

16:47.600 --> 16:49.401
Enough attitude.
Just do it.

16:50.401 --> 16:51.434
On it.

16:52.567 --> 16:54.034
Feel like I'm gonna puke.

16:54.167 --> 16:56.734
Don't, because he will
just make me clean it.

16:56.867 --> 16:59.401
This is our only shot.
It's here or nowhere.

16:59.533 --> 17:01.567
- Hey. Come on.
- Okay. You guys ready?

17:01.700 --> 17:04.201
- Yeah. - Yeah.
- Okay, on three.

17:04.334 --> 17:07.201
One, two, three.

17:30.034 --> 17:32.900
No.

17:33.034 --> 17:34.667
You?

17:34.800 --> 17:36.834
"In light of recent controversy,

17:36.967 --> 17:42.067
we are unable to consider
your application at this time."

17:42.201 --> 17:43.633
This is so not fair.

17:43.767 --> 17:46.401
I mean, this is so not fair.
I didn't do anything wrong.

17:46.533 --> 17:48.567
You guys definitely
didn't do anything wrong.

17:48.700 --> 17:52.401
Expect disappointment and
you will never get disappointed.

17:53.834 --> 17:55.700
♪ No sleep till ♪

17:58.934 --> 18:00.234
♪ Boston ♪

18:05.034 --> 18:06.468
You guys didn't get in?

18:06.600 --> 18:09.267
Yeah, because we're actually
friends with Spider-Man.

18:11.434 --> 18:13.600
Uh, yeah. I better get going.

18:13.734 --> 18:16.734
There's a mixer
for new admissions and...

18:16.867 --> 18:18.734
Sorry, guys.

18:18.867 --> 18:20.633
Jones, what are you doing?
Get back to work.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.267
Yeah, I'm coming.

18:22.401 --> 18:23.434
Know what?

18:25.234 --> 18:27.001
I wouldn't change
a thing I did.

18:28.468 --> 18:29.734
Me neither.

18:32.667 --> 18:35.301
Although I do need to show
this letter to my parents.

19:45.101 --> 19:46.900
Um, hi.

19:50.034 --> 19:51.067
Hi?

19:52.101 --> 19:53.567
I'm, uh...

19:53.700 --> 19:55.734
The most famous person
in the world.

19:55.867 --> 19:56.900
I know.

19:57.900 --> 19:59.700
Wong. Try not to slip.

19:59.834 --> 20:01.533
We don't have
liability insurance.

20:04.900 --> 20:06.533
Is all this
for a holiday party?

20:06.667 --> 20:10.633
No. One of the rotunda
gateways connects to Siberia.

20:10.767 --> 20:12.533
A blizzard blasted through.

20:14.500 --> 20:17.101
Because someone forgot to cast
a monthly maintenance spell

20:17.234 --> 20:18.600
to keep the seals tight.

20:18.734 --> 20:20.567
That's right, he did,
because he forgot

20:20.700 --> 20:22.967
- I now have higher duties.
- Higher duties?

20:23.101 --> 20:25.301
The Sorcerer Supreme
has higher duties. Yes.

20:25.434 --> 20:27.567
Wait, I thought you were
the Sorcerer Supreme.

20:27.700 --> 20:29.267
No, he got it
on a technicality

20:29.401 --> 20:30.934
because I blipped
for five years.

20:31.067 --> 20:33.934
- Oh, well, congratulations.
- If I'd been here, then...

20:34.067 --> 20:35.167
You'd burn the place down.

20:35.301 --> 20:37.600
You two, no one said
stop shoveling.

20:37.734 --> 20:40.800
So, Peter, to what
do I owe the pleasure?

20:40.934 --> 20:43.934
Right. I'm really sorry
to bother you, sir.

20:44.067 --> 20:46.134
Please. We saved half
the universe together.

20:46.267 --> 20:48.134
Think we're beyond
you calling me "sir."

20:48.267 --> 20:49.800
Okay, uh, Stephen.

20:49.934 --> 20:51.800
That feels weird,
but I'll allow it.

20:54.401 --> 20:56.034
When...

20:56.167 --> 20:59.101
When Mysterio
revealed my identity...

20:59.234 --> 21:02.767
my entire life got screwed up
and I was wondering...

21:02.900 --> 21:04.767
I don't know
if this would actually work,

21:04.900 --> 21:07.267
but I was wondering if...

21:07.401 --> 21:11.067
maybe you could go back in time
and make it so he never did?

21:12.434 --> 21:13.867
Peter...

21:14.001 --> 21:16.468
we tampered with the stability
of space-time

21:16.600 --> 21:18.134
to resurrect countless lives.

21:18.267 --> 21:20.567
You wanna do it again now
because yours got messy?

21:20.700 --> 21:22.101
It's not about me.

21:22.234 --> 21:24.633
I mean, this is really hurting
a lot of people.

21:24.767 --> 21:27.267
My Aunt May, Happy,

21:27.401 --> 21:28.900
my best friend,
my girlfriend,

21:29.034 --> 21:31.434
their futures are ruined
just because they know me,

21:31.567 --> 21:32.967
and they've done
nothing wrong.

21:33.101 --> 21:35.134
I am so sorry...

21:36.201 --> 21:38.267
but even if I wanted to...

21:38.401 --> 21:40.834
I don't have
the Time Stone anymore.

21:43.101 --> 21:44.134
That's right.

21:47.867 --> 21:50.800
I'm really sorry
if I wasted your time.

21:50.934 --> 21:53.500
- No. You didn't.
- Just forget about it.

21:53.633 --> 21:56.500
He will. He's very good
at forgetting things.

21:58.067 --> 22:00.900
Wong, you've actually
generated a good idea.

22:01.034 --> 22:01.967
What?

22:02.101 --> 22:04.134
The Runes of Kof-Kol.

22:04.267 --> 22:05.867
The Runes of Kof-Kol?

22:06.001 --> 22:07.900
It's just a standard
spell of forgetting.

22:08.034 --> 22:10.067
Won't turn back time,
but people will forget

22:10.201 --> 22:11.301
you were ever Spider-Man.

22:11.434 --> 22:13.301
- Seriously?
- No, not seriously.

22:13.434 --> 22:15.201
That spell travels
the dark borders

22:15.334 --> 22:16.967
between known
and unknown reality.

22:17.101 --> 22:18.368
It's too dangerous.

22:19.368 --> 22:20.967
We've used it for a lot less.

22:21.101 --> 22:23.201
Do you remember the full moon
party at Kamar-Taj?

22:23.334 --> 22:24.934
- No.
- Exactly.

22:28.301 --> 22:29.900
Come on, Wong.

22:31.368 --> 22:33.234
Hasn't he been through enough?

22:40.267 --> 22:42.500
Just leave me out of this.

22:42.633 --> 22:43.667
Fine.

22:44.900 --> 22:45.934
Fine.

22:57.967 --> 23:00.267
So, what is this place?

23:00.401 --> 23:02.434
The Sanctum's built
at the intersection

23:02.567 --> 23:04.201
of cosmic energy currents.

23:04.334 --> 23:06.533
We weren't the first
to seek them out.

23:06.667 --> 23:10.034
Some of these walls
are thousands of years old.

23:10.167 --> 23:13.633
And they shot an episode of
<i>The Equalizer</i> here in the '80s.

23:13.767 --> 23:14.800
Well, I, um...

23:16.700 --> 23:19.267
really appreciate you
doing this for me, sir.

23:19.401 --> 23:20.468
Don't mention it.

23:22.201 --> 23:24.533
And don't call me "sir."

23:24.667 --> 23:26.401
Right. Sorry.

23:26.533 --> 23:27.800
You ready?

23:28.867 --> 23:29.900
I'm ready.

23:31.934 --> 23:34.001
Nice knowing you, Spider-Man.

23:38.101 --> 23:39.633
Wait, excuse me?

23:41.034 --> 23:42.567
The entire world's
about to forget

23:42.700 --> 23:45.101
that Peter Parker
is Spider-Man.

23:45.234 --> 23:46.633
- Including me.
- Everyone?

23:46.767 --> 23:49.434
Uh, can't some people
still know?

23:49.567 --> 23:51.767
That's not how
the spell works.

23:51.900 --> 23:53.468
And it's very difficult
and dangerous

23:53.600 --> 23:55.067
to change it mid-casting.

23:55.201 --> 23:57.267
So my girlfriend's
gonna forget everything?

23:57.401 --> 23:58.834
Is she even gonna be
my girlfriend?

23:58.967 --> 24:01.301
Was she your girlfriend
because you were Spider-Man?

24:01.434 --> 24:04.934
- I don't know. I really hope not.
- All right, fine.

24:05.067 --> 24:07.633
Everyone in the world's
gonna forget you're Spider-Man

24:07.767 --> 24:09.368
except your girlfriend.

24:09.500 --> 24:11.267
Thank you so much.

24:11.401 --> 24:13.368
Oh, my God, Ned. Ned.

24:14.834 --> 24:16.234
What is a Ned?

24:16.368 --> 24:17.468
He's my best friend

24:17.600 --> 24:19.800
so it's important to me
that Ned knows.

24:23.533 --> 24:27.401
Okay, let's not change
the parameters of this spell

24:27.533 --> 24:29.201
any more
while I'm casting it.

24:29.334 --> 24:31.734
Okay, I'm done.
I swear I'm done. I'm done.

24:31.867 --> 24:33.301
But my Aunt May
should really know.

24:33.434 --> 24:34.934
Peter, stop tampering
with the spell.

24:35.067 --> 24:37.434
When she found out,
it was really messy.

24:37.567 --> 24:40.101
I don't think
I could go through that again.

24:41.067 --> 24:42.401
- So my Aunt May?
- Yes.

24:42.533 --> 24:43.767
Thank you. Happy?

24:43.900 --> 24:45.134
No, I'm annoyed.

24:45.267 --> 24:47.067
No, it's a nickname.
Harold "Happy" Hogan.

24:47.201 --> 24:49.334
He used to work with Tony Stark,
but then he was...

24:49.468 --> 24:51.734
Could you just stop talking?

24:59.201 --> 25:00.934
Basically everyone that knew

25:01.067 --> 25:03.567
I was Spider-Man before
should still know!

25:24.067 --> 25:25.434
- Did it work?
- No.

25:25.567 --> 25:28.368
You changed my spell six times.

25:28.500 --> 25:30.067
- Five times.
- You changed my spell.

25:30.201 --> 25:33.533
You don't do that. I told you.
And that is why.

25:33.667 --> 25:36.267
That spell was out of control.
If I hadn't shut it down,

25:36.401 --> 25:38.667
something catastrophic
could have happened.

25:38.800 --> 25:42.101
- Stephen, listen, I am so...
- Call me "sir."

25:43.967 --> 25:45.234
Sorry, sir.

25:46.468 --> 25:48.167
After everything
we've been through,

25:48.301 --> 25:52.468
somehow I always forget
you're just a kid.

25:52.600 --> 25:55.633
Look, Parker, the problem
is not Mysterio.

25:55.767 --> 25:57.967
It's you trying to live
two different lives.

25:58.101 --> 26:00.500
And the longer you do that,
the more dangerous it becomes.

26:00.633 --> 26:02.567
Believe me. I'm so sorry

26:02.700 --> 26:05.734
about you and your friends
not getting into college,

26:05.867 --> 26:08.867
but if they rejected you
and you tried

26:09.001 --> 26:10.401
to convince them to reconsider,

26:10.533 --> 26:12.734
there's nothing else
you can do.

26:15.900 --> 26:17.767
When you say, "Convince them,"

26:17.900 --> 26:20.900
- you mean I could have called them?
- Yeah.

26:21.034 --> 26:22.201
I could do that?

26:23.734 --> 26:25.533
You haven't called the...?

26:25.667 --> 26:27.368
I got their letter.
I assumed that was...

26:27.500 --> 26:30.867
I'm sorry.
Are you telling me

26:31.001 --> 26:33.867
that you didn't even think to
plead your case with them first

26:34.001 --> 26:37.633
before you asked me
to brainwash the entire world?

26:40.234 --> 26:42.334
Well, I mean,
when you put it like that...

26:50.101 --> 26:51.600
Come on, pick up, pick up.

26:51.734 --> 26:53.101
Dude, what? I'm busy.

26:53.234 --> 26:55.401
- Flash, where's the MIT mixer?
- <i>Why?</i>

26:55.533 --> 26:57.134
Because I need
to talk to someone.

26:57.267 --> 26:59.001
I'm trying to get Ned and MJ
a second chance at getting in.

26:59.134 --> 27:00.468
What's in it for me?

27:00.600 --> 27:02.301
<i>I'm risking a lot
just talking to you.</i>

27:02.434 --> 27:05.301
Okay, I will, um...

27:05.434 --> 27:07.900
pick you up and swing you
to school for one week?

27:08.034 --> 27:09.234
For a month.

27:09.368 --> 27:11.101
- <i>For a week.</i>
- Two weeks.

27:11.234 --> 27:14.101
- Flash, please. Help me.
- You know what I want.

27:15.600 --> 27:17.533
Okay, I'll tell everyone
you're my best friend.

27:17.667 --> 27:19.567
- <i>Flash, please help me.</i>
- Cool, cool, cool.

27:19.700 --> 27:21.234
<i>There's the
assistant vice chancellor.</i>

27:21.368 --> 27:22.633
<i>You can plead your case
with her.</i>

27:22.767 --> 27:24.434
- Perfect. Where is she?
- She left.

27:24.567 --> 27:26.267
- To go where?
- To the airport.

27:33.001 --> 27:35.267
<i>Stark network unavailable.</i>

27:35.401 --> 27:37.900
<i>Facial recognition unavailable.</i>

27:41.234 --> 27:42.267
Hi.

27:44.201 --> 27:46.134
Yeah, I can see you.

27:56.134 --> 27:57.301
Oh, my God.

27:59.633 --> 28:01.167
- That's Peter Parker.
- Mom.

28:01.301 --> 28:02.834
- Mom, look.
- Mommy.

28:02.967 --> 28:04.600
No, it's Peter Parker.

28:14.234 --> 28:15.633
Hey.

28:15.767 --> 28:17.101
Okay.

28:17.234 --> 28:18.800
Whew.

28:27.667 --> 28:30.567
- Yeah.
- Hi. I'm Peter Parker.

28:30.700 --> 28:32.301
You do know you're
in the street, right?

28:32.434 --> 28:34.533
Yeah, I'm sorry. I really
needed to talk to you

28:34.667 --> 28:36.434
and I know you're
on your way to the airport.

28:36.567 --> 28:40.067
MJ Watson and Ned Leeds are the
two smartest people I've met,

28:40.201 --> 28:42.500
and I'm the dumbest person
because I let them help me,

28:42.633 --> 28:44.500
but if I didn't,
millions would've died,

28:44.633 --> 28:46.734
so please don't let MIT
be dumb like me.

28:46.867 --> 28:47.900
MIT is dumb?

28:48.034 --> 28:50.800
No, I'm saying
don't let MIT be dumb.

28:50.934 --> 28:53.234
I mean, like
the dumber version of me

28:53.368 --> 28:55.500
that wouldn't have
let them help.

28:56.800 --> 28:58.667
You didn't rehearse that,
did you, Peter?

29:00.434 --> 29:01.967
Basically, what I'm trying to...

29:10.101 --> 29:11.401
Why are you running?

29:15.401 --> 29:16.934
Oh, my God.

29:17.067 --> 29:18.967
Ma'am, you should get out
of the car.

29:19.101 --> 29:21.301
Everybody get off the bridge!

29:23.201 --> 29:24.234
The door's locked.

29:24.368 --> 29:26.101
Door's... Hey!

29:42.934 --> 29:44.234
Hello, Peter.

29:45.267 --> 29:47.167
Hi? Do we...? Do I know you?

29:47.301 --> 29:49.500
What have you done
with my machine?

29:49.633 --> 29:52.434
I don't know what you're
talking about. What machine?

29:52.567 --> 29:55.468
The power of the sun
in the palm of my hand.

29:55.600 --> 29:56.834
It's gone.

29:56.967 --> 29:59.001
Listen, sir,
if you stop smashing cars,

29:59.134 --> 30:01.734
we can work together and I can
help you find your machine.

30:01.867 --> 30:03.434
You want to play games?

30:06.034 --> 30:07.167
Catch.

30:24.167 --> 30:26.567
It's okay. You guys are good.
You're safe. Get out.

30:26.700 --> 30:30.234
You think your fancy new suit's
gonna save you?

30:44.067 --> 30:45.934
Should've killed
your little girlfriend

30:46.067 --> 30:47.301
when I had the chance.

30:51.201 --> 30:52.567
What did you just say?

30:52.700 --> 30:54.934
Looks like we got competition.

31:14.767 --> 31:17.101
Peter! Help!

31:38.934 --> 31:41.034
Don't worry, ma'am! I'm coming!

31:43.167 --> 31:44.368
Peter!

32:11.267 --> 32:12.767
Ma'am, just stay calm.

32:12.900 --> 32:14.001
Just take
a deep breath.

32:14.134 --> 32:16.334
- Are you okay?
- No!

32:18.201 --> 32:20.800
I promise, I've got this
all under control.

32:27.500 --> 32:29.567
<i>Suit compromised.</i>

32:29.700 --> 32:31.734
Nanotechnology.

32:31.867 --> 32:34.067
Ah, you've outdone yourself,
Peter.

32:40.500 --> 32:42.201
I underestimated you.

32:43.401 --> 32:44.867
But now you die.

33:01.034 --> 33:02.500
You're not Peter Parker.

33:02.633 --> 33:05.101
I am so confused right now.

33:07.401 --> 33:08.767
What's happening?

33:08.900 --> 33:10.401
<i>New device detected.</i>

33:12.600 --> 33:13.834
<i>Pairing new device.</i>

33:17.633 --> 33:20.567
You don't listen to him.
You listen to me.

33:26.401 --> 33:27.434
Hey.

33:34.700 --> 33:35.934
Whoa.

33:40.401 --> 33:42.067
Hey. Hey!

33:42.201 --> 33:43.967
Listen to me.

33:44.101 --> 33:46.067
No, not him.
Me.

33:52.867 --> 33:54.134
Ma'am, you okay?

33:54.267 --> 33:56.734
Come on, you can still
make your flight.

33:56.867 --> 33:57.900
Peter.

33:59.468 --> 34:00.500
You're a hero.

34:00.633 --> 34:03.001
No. Well, I'm... No, I'm...

34:03.134 --> 34:05.900
I'm gonna talk to Admissions
about your friends.

34:06.034 --> 34:08.401
And I'm gonna talk
to them about you.

34:08.533 --> 34:10.633
But, ma'am,
this isn't about me.

34:10.767 --> 34:14.667
I am going to talk to them
about your friends and you.

34:14.800 --> 34:16.334
- Okay?
- Really?

34:16.468 --> 34:17.967
And if you keep
your noses clean,

34:18.101 --> 34:19.500
maybe you'll have a fair shot.

34:19.633 --> 34:22.101
Here. Get out of the way.
Let me get that man.

34:22.234 --> 34:24.101
Hey! You! I see you.
Come here!

34:24.234 --> 34:26.767
That was not okay.
Unbelievable.

34:28.101 --> 34:29.267
Who are...?

34:29.401 --> 34:30.533
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

34:30.667 --> 34:32.301
Until you stop
trying to kill me,

34:32.434 --> 34:33.468
I'm in control, buddy,

34:33.600 --> 34:35.533
of this whole
tentacle situation

34:35.667 --> 34:37.267
you got going on here,
okay?

34:37.401 --> 34:39.401
Now, who are you?
What is going...?

34:48.767 --> 34:49.800
No.

34:56.700 --> 34:57.967
Osborn?

35:20.767 --> 35:21.633
Doctor...?

35:29.500 --> 35:33.633
Be careful
what you wish for, Parker.

35:33.767 --> 35:35.267
Let me out of here!

35:35.401 --> 35:37.401
Can you please explain to me
what is going on?

35:37.533 --> 35:39.101
That little spell
that you botched

35:39.234 --> 35:40.633
where you wanted
everyone to forget

35:40.767 --> 35:41.967
that Peter Parker's
Spider-Man,

35:42.101 --> 35:43.401
it started pulling in
everyone

35:43.533 --> 35:44.967
who knows
Peter Parker's Spider-Man

35:45.101 --> 35:48.734
from every universe
into this one.

35:48.867 --> 35:51.767
- From every universe?
- Who are you? And where am I?

35:51.900 --> 35:53.267
I think it's
better we don't engage

35:53.401 --> 35:54.600
with them because,
frankly,

35:54.734 --> 35:56.533
the multiverse
is a concept about which

35:56.667 --> 35:59.101
we know frighteningly little.

35:59.234 --> 36:01.401
The multiverse is real?

36:01.533 --> 36:03.134
This shouldn't even be possible.

36:03.267 --> 36:05.468
- I thought you stopped the spell.
- No, I contained it.

36:05.600 --> 36:07.800
It would appear
a few of them squeaked through.

36:07.934 --> 36:10.167
After you left, I detected
an otherworldly presence.

36:10.301 --> 36:13.600
I pursued it into the sewers,
where I found that...

36:13.734 --> 36:16.101
slimy green son of a gun.

36:16.234 --> 36:18.967
Spell? As in magic?

36:19.101 --> 36:21.001
What is this,
a birthday party?

36:21.134 --> 36:23.567
Who is this clown?
What is this madness?

36:23.700 --> 36:25.934
Watch this.
Do you know a Peter Parker

36:26.067 --> 36:27.834
- who's Spider-Man?
- Yes.

36:27.967 --> 36:29.267
- Is that him?
- No.

36:29.401 --> 36:30.767
See?

36:31.767 --> 36:33.267
Okay, here's what we gotta do.

36:33.401 --> 36:35.633
I don't know how many
visitors we've got...

36:35.767 --> 36:38.267
I saw another one
on the bridge.

36:38.401 --> 36:41.867
He was like a
flying green elf.

36:42.001 --> 36:43.934
He sounds jolly.
Start with him.

36:44.067 --> 36:45.234
I need you
to capture them,

36:45.368 --> 36:46.800
bring them here
while I figure out

36:46.934 --> 36:48.368
how to get them back
before

36:48.500 --> 36:50.434
they destroy
the fabric of reality,

36:50.567 --> 36:52.767
or worse, Wong finds out.

36:52.900 --> 36:54.468
Uh, Doctor Strange?

36:54.600 --> 36:56.267
What?

36:56.401 --> 36:59.267
My friends and I just got a
second chance to get into MIT,

36:59.401 --> 37:02.134
and if the school sees me
fighting these crazy monsters...

37:02.267 --> 37:03.934
- Hey, watch your mouth.
- I'm sorry but...

37:04.067 --> 37:06.434
Are you seriously
still talking about college?

37:12.034 --> 37:14.334
- Hey, what did you just do?
- This.

37:15.934 --> 37:17.101
Hey, you can't just...

37:20.101 --> 37:21.167
How did you do that?

37:21.301 --> 37:23.301
Lots of birthday parties.

37:29.567 --> 37:30.633
Hey.

37:32.667 --> 37:33.734
Whoa.

37:33.867 --> 37:35.401
One shot,
send them here, move on.

37:35.533 --> 37:36.867
You're welcome. Get to work.

37:37.001 --> 37:37.867
Sir?

37:38.001 --> 37:40.767
Now what?

37:40.900 --> 37:43.567
I know this is my mess,
and I swear to you I'll fix it,

37:43.700 --> 37:45.267
but I'm gonna need help.

37:46.567 --> 37:48.034
Whoa!

37:48.167 --> 37:50.800
I can't believe
I'm in the Sanctum Sanctorum.

37:50.934 --> 37:52.600
Neither can I.

37:52.734 --> 37:55.301
So how did you know
you were a man of magic?

37:55.434 --> 37:57.600
Because my nana says
that we have it in our family,

37:57.734 --> 37:59.533
and I get these tinglings
in my hands...

37:59.667 --> 38:00.667
Talk to your physician.

38:00.800 --> 38:02.067
- Peter.
- Hey.

38:02.201 --> 38:03.967
- Hey. Hey.
- Hey. Hey.

38:04.101 --> 38:05.600
Sorry for dragging you
into this.

38:05.734 --> 38:08.468
- Help me find these guys.
- You don't have to apologize.

38:08.600 --> 38:10.633
You got us a second shot
at MIT. It's fine.

38:10.767 --> 38:13.434
So how did the bad guys
get here?

38:13.567 --> 38:16.134
We screwed up a spell
trying to get you into college.

38:16.267 --> 38:17.800
- Wait. What?
- You did it with magic?

38:17.934 --> 38:19.800
I thought it was
the MIT lady you saved.

38:19.934 --> 38:21.301
No, that was after.

38:21.434 --> 38:22.633
Let's just focus
on the good news, okay?

38:22.767 --> 38:24.468
No, let's just focus
on the bad news.

38:24.600 --> 38:28.633
As of now, you have detected
zero multiversal trespassers,

38:28.767 --> 38:32.967
so get on your phones,
scour the Internet, and...

38:33.101 --> 38:35.301
Scooby-Doo this shit.

38:35.434 --> 38:37.401
You're telling us
what to do even though

38:37.533 --> 38:39.301
it was your spell
that got screwed up,

38:39.434 --> 38:41.434
meaning that all this
is kind of your mess.

38:41.567 --> 38:44.067
I know a couple of
magic words myself,

38:44.201 --> 38:46.434
starting with
the word "please."

38:49.167 --> 38:52.401
Please Scooby-Doo this shit.

38:52.533 --> 38:54.800
You can work in the undercroft.

38:54.934 --> 38:57.301
The undercroft?

39:02.167 --> 39:03.234
Badass.

39:09.934 --> 39:12.834
- About this whole spell thing...
- It's totally okay.

39:12.967 --> 39:15.334
- Wait, really?
- Yeah. I mean, I get it.

39:15.468 --> 39:19.800
You were just trying
to fix things, and so...

39:19.934 --> 39:22.567
Maybe just run it by us
next time, you know?

39:22.700 --> 39:25.101
That way, when you're thinking,
"I'm about to do something

39:25.234 --> 39:27.900
that could break the universe,"

39:28.034 --> 39:31.767
we could, like, help you
workshop something or...

39:31.900 --> 39:34.633
brainstorm ideas.

39:36.667 --> 39:37.700
Deal.

39:39.067 --> 39:40.767
Ned?

39:40.900 --> 39:43.900
Oh, dude, I don't care.
It's seriously not a big deal.

39:44.034 --> 39:46.034
Um, oh!

39:46.167 --> 39:48.301
A torture rack.

39:50.067 --> 39:52.301
That is a Pilates machine.

39:52.434 --> 39:53.800
- That is...
- The crypt.

39:53.934 --> 39:55.967
Okay, so we get
the rest of the guys,

39:56.101 --> 39:58.067
you zap them, Doctor Magic
will send them back,

39:58.201 --> 39:59.767
and when we get into MIT,

39:59.900 --> 40:02.134
round of stale doughnuts,
my treat.

40:02.267 --> 40:03.900
Let's catch
some multiverse men.

40:04.034 --> 40:06.934
Hey! Who the hell
are these two?

40:07.067 --> 40:09.001
- My friends. This is MJ.
- Hey.

40:09.134 --> 40:10.600
- And this is Ned.
- Hello.

40:10.734 --> 40:12.567
Uh, I'm sorry,
what was your name again?

40:12.700 --> 40:14.600
Dr. Otto Octavius.

40:19.067 --> 40:21.134
Wait, no, seriously,
what's your actual name?

40:21.267 --> 40:22.767
Oh, is that
a dinosaur?

40:44.734 --> 40:46.800
<i>If the paint
won't come off, I'll get it out.</i>

40:46.934 --> 40:49.934
No, no, no. May. We gotta
find these guys first.

40:50.067 --> 40:52.101
<i>Well, finish your mission,
and then come by.</i>

40:52.234 --> 40:54.267
<i>We're having
a canned food drive.</i>

40:54.401 --> 40:56.301
- That could work.
- I got one.

40:56.434 --> 40:57.867
- May, I gotta go.
- <i>Okay.</i>

40:58.001 --> 41:00.034
I mean, you can take
the guy out of the chair,

41:00.167 --> 41:02.234
but you can't take
the chair out of the guy.

41:02.368 --> 41:04.700
- What'd you find?
- There's a...

41:04.834 --> 41:07.301
A disturbance near
a military research facility

41:07.434 --> 41:08.567
outside of the city,

41:08.700 --> 41:10.301
and witnesses say
that they saw

41:10.434 --> 41:12.401
a monster flying
through the air.

41:13.900 --> 41:15.967
It's gotta be the guy
I saw on the bridge, right?

41:16.101 --> 41:17.334
That's impossible.

41:19.767 --> 41:21.001
You know him, don't you?

41:22.134 --> 41:24.767
On the bridge,
you said his name.

41:24.900 --> 41:27.500
Norman Osborn.

41:27.633 --> 41:32.067
Brilliant scientist.
Military research.

41:32.201 --> 41:35.500
But he was greedy, misguided.

41:35.633 --> 41:39.900
- What happened to him?
- We tire of your questions, boy!

41:40.034 --> 41:42.567
Okay, um...

41:42.700 --> 41:44.934
I gotta go. Where am I going?

41:45.067 --> 41:46.101
It can't be him.

41:47.734 --> 41:49.368
Why?

41:49.500 --> 41:52.967
Because Norman Osborn
died years ago.

41:54.234 --> 41:57.800
So either we saw someone else...

41:57.934 --> 42:02.767
or you're flying out into
the darkness to fight a ghost.

42:26.234 --> 42:29.500
Keep an eye out on the trees.
We don't know where this guy is.

42:32.134 --> 42:35.434
<i>I genuinely don't know how you
do this without throwing up.</i>

42:52.867 --> 42:54.034
Did you guys see that?

42:54.167 --> 42:56.234
<i>Um, no.</i>

42:56.368 --> 42:58.067
<i>It's-It's really dark.</i>

43:10.067 --> 43:11.800
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

43:18.600 --> 43:19.800
<i>What-What's happening?</i>

43:19.934 --> 43:21.067
<i>Peter, what is it?</i>

43:23.468 --> 43:24.967
<i>Are you getting
the tingle thing?</i>

43:25.101 --> 43:27.468
<i>Is the tingle happening?
Is your tingle tingling?</i>

43:36.600 --> 43:38.734
- Are you guys seeing this?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

43:38.867 --> 43:39.967
<i>Osborn?</i>

43:40.101 --> 43:43.101
No. He was green.
This guy's blue.

43:43.234 --> 43:46.201
You wouldn't happen to be from
another universe, would you?

43:47.167 --> 43:48.600
<i>What's he doing?</i>

43:48.734 --> 43:50.301
<i>I don't know.
Looks like he's charging.</i>

43:50.434 --> 43:52.368
I don't like this.
Just web him.

43:57.834 --> 43:59.234
Whoa!

44:04.834 --> 44:08.067
<i>Go left! Left, dude, left!
Left! Go! Left! Yes!</i>

44:08.201 --> 44:10.134
<i>What are you talking about?
Right.</i>

44:10.267 --> 44:12.533
<i>Go to the right! Right!
Right! He means right.</i>

44:12.667 --> 44:15.867
- <i>Don't listen to him.</i>
- Guys, this is not helping!

44:22.368 --> 44:25.234
Oh, no, no, no.
What happened? Peter? Peter.

44:32.301 --> 44:33.567
Whoa.

44:33.700 --> 44:38.234
Peter, it's me, Flint Marko.
You remember?

44:38.368 --> 44:39.900
I'm Peter,
but I'm not your Peter.

44:40.034 --> 44:41.567
What do you mean,
you're not my Peter?

44:41.700 --> 44:43.267
What the hell is going on?

44:43.401 --> 44:45.633
I'll explain, but first,
can you help me?

44:45.767 --> 44:47.600
- Okay.
- You try to surround him,

44:47.734 --> 44:50.067
and I'll pull the plug.
All right, let's go!

45:04.001 --> 45:07.600
I can't hold him much longer.

45:07.734 --> 45:09.301
I got it, I got it!

45:36.900 --> 45:39.134
Different Peter. Weird.

45:39.267 --> 45:42.434
- Thanks. Sorry.
- Don't worry about it.

45:50.667 --> 45:52.867
I got my body back.

45:53.001 --> 45:54.633
Hey, um...

45:54.767 --> 45:56.567
This is gonna sound
really crazy,

45:56.700 --> 45:58.267
but this isn't your universe.

45:58.401 --> 45:59.600
Another universe?

45:59.734 --> 46:00.734
- Uh-huh.
- What?

46:00.867 --> 46:02.700
That's what I was feeling.

46:02.834 --> 46:04.967
The power, it's different.

46:06.700 --> 46:07.734
I like it.

46:09.900 --> 46:11.234
Easy, buddy.

46:11.368 --> 46:13.234
It's actually my fault
that you're here.

46:13.368 --> 46:17.101
Like, the universe or the woods?

46:17.234 --> 46:18.101
I hate the woods.

46:18.234 --> 46:20.101
I meant the universe, sir.

46:20.234 --> 46:21.900
So, what, y'all
just gonna stand here

46:22.034 --> 46:23.600
and act like I ain't
butt-ass naked?

46:23.734 --> 46:25.900
- I am.
- No, no.

46:26.034 --> 46:27.101
I, uh...

46:38.967 --> 46:41.600
What was that?
What did you just do to him?

46:41.734 --> 46:43.667
- No. It's okay.
- Did you kill him?

46:43.800 --> 46:45.434
I can explain everything.
Trust me.

46:45.567 --> 46:46.900
Please just trust me.

46:47.034 --> 46:48.900
I don't trust you.
I don't know you.

46:51.867 --> 46:52.967
What is this?

46:54.267 --> 46:55.767
You picked the wrong side.

46:58.500 --> 46:59.700
Connors?

47:01.167 --> 47:03.267
Wait. You know this creature?

47:03.401 --> 47:07.468
No, no, no.
Not a creature. A man.

47:07.600 --> 47:08.800
The same universes.

47:08.934 --> 47:10.967
Dr. Curt Connors.
He was a scientist

47:11.101 --> 47:12.867
at Oscorp when I worked there.

47:13.001 --> 47:14.967
A brilliant scientist.

47:15.101 --> 47:16.700
Until he turned himself
into a lizard.

47:16.834 --> 47:18.900
Then he tried to turn
the whole city into lizards.

47:19.034 --> 47:21.401
- It was crazy.
- It wasn't crazy, Max.

47:21.533 --> 47:23.600
It was the next step
in human evolution.

47:23.734 --> 47:25.767
- The dinosaur can talk. Right.
- Lizard.

47:25.900 --> 47:27.700
Speaking of which
what happened to you?

47:27.834 --> 47:29.667
Last I recall,
you had bad teeth,

47:29.800 --> 47:31.267
glasses and a comb-over.

47:31.401 --> 47:33.900
Did you get a makeover?

47:34.034 --> 47:36.468
You know I can give you
a real makeover.

47:36.600 --> 47:37.934
Let me guess, into a lizard?

47:38.067 --> 47:40.567
- Exactly.
- Would you two just shut up?

47:40.700 --> 47:42.334
- Where are we?
- It's complicated.

47:42.468 --> 47:45.067
- A wizard's dungeon.
- Wizard's dungeon?

47:45.201 --> 47:46.967
There's no real way
to sugarcoat that.

47:47.101 --> 47:48.834
It's literally the dungeon
of a wizard.

47:48.967 --> 47:51.500
You can keep your magic.

47:51.633 --> 47:54.368
I want a taste of that
new energy I just felt.

47:57.734 --> 48:00.667
- Oh, Peter, hey.
- Did those guys come through yet?

48:00.800 --> 48:02.734
There should be
an electric guy and a sand guy.

48:02.867 --> 48:05.368
Yeah, they're all here
and locked up.

48:05.500 --> 48:07.134
Perfect. I'm gonna just
stay here for a bit

48:07.267 --> 48:08.468
and try and fix
some of this damage

48:08.600 --> 48:10.201
so they don't blame it
on me again.

48:10.334 --> 48:13.533
- <i>Okay.</i>
- But, hey, I, uh...

48:13.667 --> 48:16.134
I couldn't do any of this
without you, so thank you.

48:16.267 --> 48:17.234
<i>Yeah, of course.</i>

48:17.368 --> 48:19.234
Hey, ask him if this is,

48:19.368 --> 48:21.201
like, a tree monster
or, like,

48:21.334 --> 48:23.234
a scientist
that turned into a tree.

48:23.368 --> 48:26.633
It's just a tree, man.
Just a tree.

48:43.267 --> 48:46.900
<i>Coward.
We have a new world to conquer.</i>

48:49.067 --> 48:50.267
<i>You make me sick.</i>

48:50.401 --> 48:52.334
Leave me alone, please.

48:52.468 --> 48:55.500
<i>Hiding in the shadows.</i>

48:55.633 --> 48:57.867
<i>Hiding from who you truly are.</i>

48:58.001 --> 49:01.567
- No.
- <i>You can't escape yourself.</i>

49:17.500 --> 49:20.900
- Hey, May.
- <i>Hey, Peter. I'm at work, and...</i>

49:21.034 --> 49:24.067
<i>one of the guys you're
looking for just walked in.</i>

49:32.034 --> 49:33.834
May? Where's May?

49:33.967 --> 49:35.001
Thank you.

49:38.067 --> 49:39.101
May.

49:41.067 --> 49:42.734
Ah, hey, here he is.

49:42.867 --> 49:46.134
Norman, this is my nephew.

49:47.600 --> 49:50.134
Norman Osborn?
I thought that you were...

49:50.267 --> 49:54.734
I saw Spider-Man
in an ad for this place.

49:54.867 --> 49:57.234
And I thought
he could help me.

49:57.368 --> 49:58.600
But you're not him.

49:58.734 --> 50:01.034
Wait, so you want
Spider-Man's help?

50:01.167 --> 50:02.900
He just wandered in.

50:05.767 --> 50:07.700
I didn't know
where else to go.

50:09.167 --> 50:11.301
Someone's living in my house.

50:12.934 --> 50:14.800
Oscorp doesn't exist.

50:16.667 --> 50:17.767
My son...

50:21.834 --> 50:25.067
Sometimes I'm not myself.

50:26.201 --> 50:28.700
I'm someone else.

50:28.834 --> 50:30.834
- Mm-hm.
- And every time he's in control,

50:30.967 --> 50:33.134
- I can't remember.
- Who? Who's in control?

50:33.267 --> 50:35.101
- And now I'm here...
- Who's in control?

50:35.234 --> 50:38.301
- I don't know what's going on.
- Okay, it's okay.

50:38.434 --> 50:42.134
And I don't...
Doesn't make sense.

50:42.267 --> 50:44.001
He's lost.

50:44.134 --> 50:48.101
And I don't mean just in
the cosmos. I mean in his mind.

50:50.700 --> 50:52.633
Are they all like this?

50:52.767 --> 50:53.800
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

50:53.934 --> 50:55.334
They all have their own

50:55.468 --> 50:57.267
mental or physical issues.

50:57.401 --> 51:01.101
Oh, well, he needs help
and maybe they all do.

51:01.234 --> 51:04.401
Wait, you don't mean...?
No, May, this isn't my problem.

51:04.533 --> 51:07.301
Peter, not your problem? Hmm?

51:07.434 --> 51:10.101
May. Their chance
of getting help is way better

51:10.234 --> 51:12.067
back where they came from.

51:12.201 --> 51:13.734
Sending them home,

51:13.867 --> 51:15.800
that's the best thing
we can do for them.

51:15.934 --> 51:18.600
For them? Or for yourself?

51:21.267 --> 51:24.468
Look around you.
This is what we do.

51:24.600 --> 51:29.368
- We help people.
- This is what's best for them.

51:29.500 --> 51:30.967
Trust me.

51:33.201 --> 51:37.667
<i>But the fact remains,
Spider-Man is a menace.</i>

51:37.800 --> 51:39.934
We'll be right back
after a brief word

51:40.067 --> 51:41.967
from <i>Daily Bugle</i> Supplements.

51:42.101 --> 51:44.834
The only other daily fix
you need.

51:44.967 --> 51:46.800
And we're out.

51:48.900 --> 51:49.900
What?

51:52.900 --> 51:54.167
I got eyes on him.

51:54.301 --> 51:55.834
<i>He's with his aunt
and some guy.</i>

51:55.967 --> 51:57.934
- You sure?
- <i>They're leaving the shelter.</i>

51:58.067 --> 51:59.734
Okay. Don't lose him.

52:10.368 --> 52:13.434
Thanks, May.
Hope to see you again.

52:13.567 --> 52:17.567
Hey. He trusts you. So do I.

52:19.667 --> 52:21.900
Thanks for cleaning my suit.

52:22.034 --> 52:23.434
I'll see you later.

52:25.533 --> 52:28.301
- Um, guys, this is Mr. Osborn.
- Hey, it's "doctor."

52:28.434 --> 52:30.600
Sorry. Um, Dr. Osborn,
these are my friends.

52:30.734 --> 52:32.567
This is Ned and MJ.

52:32.700 --> 52:36.434
- Mary Jane?
- It's Michelle Jones, actually.

52:37.967 --> 52:39.633
Fascinating.

52:43.567 --> 52:45.734
Do you think
there are other Ned Leedses?

52:59.067 --> 53:00.434
Octavius?

53:04.434 --> 53:06.368
Osborn?

53:06.500 --> 53:10.434
- What... What happened to you?
- What happened to...?

53:10.567 --> 53:13.234
- You're the walking corpse.
- What do you mean?

53:13.368 --> 53:15.867
You died, Norman.

53:16.001 --> 53:17.633
Years ago.

53:18.600 --> 53:20.101
You're insane.

53:20.234 --> 53:23.267
- God, I love it here.
- What are you talking about?

53:23.401 --> 53:25.101
He's standing right there.
He's not...

53:25.234 --> 53:28.034
Dead. They both died,

53:28.167 --> 53:30.134
fighting Spider-Man.

53:33.167 --> 53:35.468
It was all over the news.

53:35.600 --> 53:40.334
Green Goblin, impaled by
the glider you flew around on.

53:40.468 --> 53:44.734
And a couple of years later,
you, Doc Ock,

53:44.867 --> 53:46.633
drowned in the river
with your machine.

53:46.767 --> 53:48.800
That's nonsense.

53:48.934 --> 53:52.301
Spider-Man was trying
to stop my fusion reactor,

53:52.434 --> 53:54.134
so I stopped him.

53:54.267 --> 53:58.334
I had him by the throat,
and then I...

54:02.867 --> 54:05.334
- And then I was here.
- Ah, please.

54:05.468 --> 54:08.468
Let me tell you something.
I was whupping Spider-Man's ass.

54:08.600 --> 54:11.067
He'll tell you.
And then he caused an overload.

54:11.201 --> 54:13.368
I was stuck in the grid,
absorbing data.

54:13.500 --> 54:15.800
I was about to turn
into pure energy, and then...

54:15.934 --> 54:17.767
And then, uh...

54:17.900 --> 54:21.201
And then... Oh, shit.

54:21.334 --> 54:25.201
- I was about to die.
- Max, do you know? Do I die?

54:28.934 --> 54:30.800
Oh, great.
You caught another one.

54:30.934 --> 54:32.934
No, wait, Strange.
He's not dangerous.

54:35.001 --> 54:36.900
It's okay. Um...

54:39.067 --> 54:40.468
What is that?

54:40.600 --> 54:43.167
It's an ancient relic.
The Macchina di Kadavus.

54:43.301 --> 54:44.767
I trapped
your corrupted spell inside,

54:44.900 --> 54:46.667
and once I finish
the proper ritual,

54:46.800 --> 54:48.101
it'll reverse the spell

54:48.234 --> 54:50.800
and send these guys
back to their universes.

54:50.934 --> 54:53.401
And then what? We perish?

54:53.533 --> 54:55.167
No. No, thanks.
I'll pass on that.

54:55.301 --> 54:58.767
Let me out of here. Peter!

54:58.900 --> 55:03.101
Strange, we can't
send them back. Not yet.

55:03.234 --> 55:05.434
Why?

55:05.567 --> 55:07.800
Well, some of these guys
are gonna die.

55:07.934 --> 55:11.468
Parker, it's their fate.

55:12.533 --> 55:14.767
Come on, Strange, have a heart.

55:16.201 --> 55:19.134
In the grand calculus
of the multiverse,

55:19.267 --> 55:23.234
their sacrifice means infinitely
more than their lives.

55:29.001 --> 55:31.134
I'm sorry, kid.

55:31.267 --> 55:34.134
If they die, they die.

55:47.600 --> 55:48.633
Peter!

56:02.134 --> 56:03.067
Don't.

56:05.967 --> 56:08.234
- Dude, what are you doing?
- Peter, you gotta go. Go, go.

56:08.368 --> 56:09.934
- Okay.
- Get out of here.

56:11.600 --> 56:14.101
This is why I never had kids.

56:27.834 --> 56:29.567
- Give me the box.
- No.

56:30.567 --> 56:31.633
Whoa!

56:47.567 --> 56:49.734
- Oh, my God, I'm dead.
- You're not dead,

56:49.867 --> 56:52.067
you've just been separated
from your physical form.

56:52.201 --> 56:54.834
My physical... What?

56:54.967 --> 56:57.900
- How are you doing that?
- I have no idea.

56:58.034 --> 57:00.401
You should not
be able to do that.

57:00.533 --> 57:02.401
This feels amazing.

57:13.034 --> 57:14.934
That's one of the coolest
things that's happened to me,

57:15.067 --> 57:16.600
but don't ever do that again.

57:22.700 --> 57:24.567
Wha... Hey! Get off of me!

57:51.034 --> 57:52.301
<i>♪ La, la ♪</i>

57:52.434 --> 57:55.567
<i>♪ Tis the season
To be jolly... ♪</i>

58:13.234 --> 58:15.468
- What is this place?
- The Mirror Dimension,

58:15.600 --> 58:17.234
where I'm in control.

58:26.334 --> 58:28.767
Strange, stop. Can we
please just talk about this?

58:28.900 --> 58:31.867
Parker, don't you realize
that in the multiverse

58:32.001 --> 58:34.201
there are an infinite number
of people

58:34.334 --> 58:36.533
who know Peter Parker
is Spider-Man?

58:36.667 --> 58:39.468
And if that spell gets loose,
they're all coming here.

58:39.600 --> 58:42.301
I know, I get it, but we can't
just send them home to die.

58:42.434 --> 58:44.201
It's their fate.

58:44.334 --> 58:45.600
You can't change that

58:45.734 --> 58:47.734
any more than you could
change who they are.

58:47.867 --> 58:51.334
But what if we could? What if
we could change their fate?

58:51.468 --> 58:53.834
Whoa! Oh, what are you doing?

58:58.900 --> 59:00.800
I'm not giving you the... Whoa!

59:02.034 --> 59:04.334
Whoa! Whoa!

59:11.567 --> 59:13.167
Give me that back.

59:33.700 --> 59:35.934
Wait a minute.
Is that an Archimedean Spiral?

59:36.067 --> 59:37.800
The Mirror Dimension
is just geometry?

59:37.934 --> 59:40.234
You're great at geometry.
You can do geometry.

59:42.067 --> 59:43.900
Square the radius.
Divide by pi.

59:44.034 --> 59:46.967
- Plot points along the curve.
- It's over, Parker.

59:47.101 --> 59:49.567
I'll come pick you up
when it's done.

59:51.734 --> 59:53.500
Hey, Strange.

59:53.633 --> 59:55.834
You know
what's cooler than magic?

59:59.267 --> 01:00:01.633
- Math.
- Don't do this.

01:00:04.468 --> 01:00:06.667
- Ow.
- I'm sorry, sir, but...

01:00:11.101 --> 01:00:12.434
...I have to try.

01:00:15.734 --> 01:00:18.001
- What happened?
- I fought with Strange and won.

01:00:18.134 --> 01:00:20.900
- What?
- Look, I stole his ring thing.

01:00:21.034 --> 01:00:23.800
I was swinging through the city,
and then I went through

01:00:23.934 --> 01:00:25.700
this massive mirror thing,
and then I was back in...

01:00:25.834 --> 01:00:27.533
- Where is he?
- He's trapped,

01:00:27.667 --> 01:00:30.700
- but I'm not sure for how long.
- You could have left us to die.

01:00:30.834 --> 01:00:32.234
Why didn't you?

01:00:32.368 --> 01:00:33.900
Because that's not who he is.

01:00:37.201 --> 01:00:39.201
I think I can help you guys.

01:00:39.334 --> 01:00:42.034
If I can fix what happened
to you, then when you go back,

01:00:42.167 --> 01:00:43.468
things will be different,

01:00:43.600 --> 01:00:45.567
and you might not die
fighting Spider-Man.

01:00:45.700 --> 01:00:47.867
- What do you mean fix us?
- Our technology is advanced...

01:00:48.001 --> 01:00:52.468
I can help you. You know, I'm
something of a scientist myself.

01:00:54.434 --> 01:00:56.234
Octavius knows what I can do.

01:00:56.368 --> 01:00:58.900
Fix? You mean like a dog?

01:00:59.034 --> 01:01:00.301
I refuse.

01:01:00.434 --> 01:01:02.301
I can't promise
you guys anything,

01:01:02.434 --> 01:01:05.334
but at least this way, you get
to go home and have a chance.

01:01:05.468 --> 01:01:07.167
A second chance.

01:01:07.301 --> 01:01:09.101
Come on,
isn't that worth trying?

01:01:09.234 --> 01:01:12.767
Trust me, Peter,
when you try to fix people,

01:01:12.900 --> 01:01:15.600
there are always consequences.

01:01:15.734 --> 01:01:17.468
I mean, you don't have to come.

01:01:17.600 --> 01:01:19.500
I also didn't know
that you could talk.

01:01:19.633 --> 01:01:21.001
But if you stay here,

01:01:21.134 --> 01:01:22.900
you're gonna have to deal
with the wizard.

01:01:23.034 --> 01:01:27.468
Ah, so we go along or die.
Not much of a choice, is it?

01:01:27.600 --> 01:01:30.301
- I just wanna go home.
- Well, I, myself,

01:01:30.434 --> 01:01:31.900
don't wanna be killed,

01:01:32.034 --> 01:01:34.867
especially by a guy dressed
like Dungeons & Dragons,

01:01:35.001 --> 01:01:36.434
so, what's your plan?

01:01:37.834 --> 01:01:39.900
I have it all under control.

01:01:42.834 --> 01:01:45.067
What are we
gonna do about this thing?

01:01:45.201 --> 01:01:47.867
Uh, well, we need to find
somewhere safe for it, right?

01:01:48.001 --> 01:01:49.934
- Yeah, sure. You gotta take it.
- Wait, what?

01:01:50.067 --> 01:01:52.368
If something bad happens,
you just push this,

01:01:52.500 --> 01:01:55.234
- and then it's all over.
- We're not gonna leave you.

01:01:55.368 --> 01:01:57.600
You can't. It's dangerous.
You've done enough.

01:01:57.734 --> 01:02:00.001
- We're in this together.
- I know we're in this together,

01:02:00.134 --> 01:02:02.267
but I can't do this
if you're in danger.

01:02:02.401 --> 01:02:05.234
Okay? So for me, MJ,
please just take this.

01:02:08.101 --> 01:02:10.434
- Please.
- Fine.

01:02:10.567 --> 01:02:11.967
- Thank you.
- But, Peter,

01:02:12.101 --> 01:02:14.401
if I don't hear from you,
I'm pressing the button.

01:02:14.533 --> 01:02:17.834
- Sure.
- Okay. And I will do it.

01:02:17.967 --> 01:02:19.600
Yeah, we all believe you,
Michelle.

01:02:19.734 --> 01:02:22.600
No way that's his girlfriend.
No way.

01:02:22.734 --> 01:02:26.600
- She'll do it.
- Absolutely, she will.

01:02:26.734 --> 01:02:29.567
- Okay. See you later.
- Be safe.

01:02:29.700 --> 01:02:31.067
- You too.
- Okay.

01:02:32.767 --> 01:02:34.201
Whoa.

01:02:35.101 --> 01:02:36.301
Okay.

01:02:38.234 --> 01:02:39.967
- Be careful, okay?
- Yeah. You too.

01:02:47.667 --> 01:02:49.034
So, uh...

01:02:50.101 --> 01:02:51.867
who's coming with me?

01:02:55.700 --> 01:02:57.067
Well, I'm in.

01:02:57.201 --> 01:03:00.633
But if this goes sideways...

01:03:00.767 --> 01:03:03.401
I'm gonna fry you
from the inside out.

01:03:45.468 --> 01:03:46.700
<i>Where's Connors?</i>

01:03:46.834 --> 01:03:48.401
<i>He wants to stay in the truck.</i>

01:03:48.534 --> 01:03:50.034
<i>Okay.</i>

01:03:50.167 --> 01:03:52.101
<i>Alarm system deactivated.</i>

01:03:52.234 --> 01:03:54.000
Hey, May.

01:03:54.134 --> 01:03:55.733
- Yeah?
- I feel kind of bad

01:03:55.867 --> 01:03:59.034
- using Happy's place like this.
- No, no, no. He'll get over it.

01:04:00.367 --> 01:04:01.834
<i>New Yorkers</i>

01:04:01.967 --> 01:04:04.800
- <i>oppose the renovation...</i>
- Oh, sorry.

01:04:04.934 --> 01:04:08.301
So this is your plan, Peter, hm?
No lab, no facilities?

01:04:08.434 --> 01:04:11.067
Just performing miracles
in a condominium, hm?

01:04:11.201 --> 01:04:12.700
What, you gonna cook us
some cures

01:04:12.834 --> 01:04:14.633
and some frozen burritos
in a microwave?

01:04:14.767 --> 01:04:17.501
- I could go for a burrito.
- He's gonna kill us all.

01:04:17.633 --> 01:04:19.534
Well, let's hope not.

01:04:19.667 --> 01:04:21.733
- You're up first, Doc.
- What?

01:04:21.867 --> 01:04:24.134
Hey, I told you,
I don't need fixing.

01:04:24.267 --> 01:04:26.234
I don't need fixing.

01:04:26.367 --> 01:04:28.900
Especially by a teenager
using scraps

01:04:29.034 --> 01:04:30.568
from a bachelor's junk drawer.

01:04:30.700 --> 01:04:33.767
Nah, nah, nah.
He got something back there.

01:04:33.900 --> 01:04:36.334
I can feel it.
That weird energy.

01:04:37.733 --> 01:04:38.867
What the hell is that?

01:04:39.000 --> 01:04:40.733
It's a fabricator.

01:04:40.867 --> 01:04:45.234
It can analyze, design,
construct basically anything.

01:04:45.367 --> 01:04:47.568
I thought that was
the tanning bed Happy broke.

01:04:50.468 --> 01:04:51.568
Look at that.

01:04:58.900 --> 01:05:00.434
He's gonna kill us all.

01:05:08.534 --> 01:05:10.967
Whoa. What's going on there?

01:05:11.101 --> 01:05:13.367
So the chip in
the back of Doc's neck

01:05:13.501 --> 01:05:15.800
was designed to protect
his brain from the AI system

01:05:15.934 --> 01:05:17.367
that's controlling
these tentacles,

01:05:17.501 --> 01:05:21.534
but if you look here...
the chip is fried.

01:05:21.667 --> 01:05:24.167
So rather than him being
in control of the tentacles,

01:05:24.301 --> 01:05:26.234
the tentacles are now
in control of him.

01:05:26.367 --> 01:05:31.501
Which, I guess, explains why
he is so miserable all the time.

01:05:39.834 --> 01:05:41.101
Thirsty?

01:05:43.967 --> 01:05:46.034
Well, yes, I am thirsty.

01:05:46.167 --> 01:05:48.434
Fresh water or salt?

01:05:48.568 --> 01:05:50.600
You know,
because you're an octopus.

01:05:52.301 --> 01:05:53.534
What?

01:05:54.867 --> 01:05:56.334
Fresh water it is.

01:05:57.367 --> 01:05:59.267
Look at this place.

01:05:59.401 --> 01:06:02.568
- And all the possibilities.
- What, this condo?

01:06:02.700 --> 01:06:05.733
Yeah, yeah, the condo. I love
the whole open floor plan. No.

01:06:05.867 --> 01:06:08.867
No, man,
I'm talking about the world.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:11.301
I kind of like who I am here.

01:06:12.800 --> 01:06:15.468
And all that power back there...

01:06:15.600 --> 01:06:17.534
I could be so much more.

01:06:17.667 --> 01:06:19.401
So why'd you come along?

01:06:19.534 --> 01:06:22.401
I have a daughter,
and I want to see her.

01:06:22.534 --> 01:06:24.633
But he's not gonna
send anyone home

01:06:24.767 --> 01:06:28.000
till he's finished his little
science project back there.

01:06:28.134 --> 01:06:29.334
You trust him?

01:06:29.468 --> 01:06:31.000
I don't trust anyone.

01:06:32.167 --> 01:06:33.700
How'd you end up
like that anyway?

01:06:33.834 --> 01:06:35.568
Oh...

01:06:35.700 --> 01:06:37.434
the place where I worked at,

01:06:37.568 --> 01:06:39.934
they were experimenting
with electricity

01:06:40.067 --> 01:06:43.167
created by living organisms,
and then, uh...

01:06:43.301 --> 01:06:45.501
I fell into
a vat of electric eels.

01:06:45.633 --> 01:06:48.568
You're kidding.
I fell into a supercollider.

01:06:48.700 --> 01:06:50.434
Damn.

01:06:50.568 --> 01:06:52.401
Gotta be careful
where you fall.

01:06:53.334 --> 01:06:54.934
Remarkable.

01:06:56.468 --> 01:06:58.900
The technology and you.

01:07:01.201 --> 01:07:04.367
When all this is over,
if you need a job

01:07:04.501 --> 01:07:09.201
and you're willing to commute
to another universe...

01:07:14.434 --> 01:07:17.301
It worked. That totally worked.

01:07:17.434 --> 01:07:19.834
I got it. I did it.
Uh, will you send him up?

01:07:19.967 --> 01:07:21.334
Here we go.

01:07:22.367 --> 01:07:23.800
- Sorry.
- Hold on, Doc.

01:07:23.934 --> 01:07:26.501
Oh, will these humiliations
never cease?

01:07:26.633 --> 01:07:29.534
You, keep your science fair
project away from me!

01:07:29.667 --> 01:07:31.234
It'll work. Have faith.

01:07:31.367 --> 01:07:34.334
Says the reckless fool who
turned himself into a monster.

01:07:35.600 --> 01:07:37.501
Please stop moving your head.

01:07:37.633 --> 01:07:40.101
- Hold still.
- Don't you dare.

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:47.367
Ugh! I swear,
when I get out of this,

01:07:47.501 --> 01:07:49.867
we're gonna rip you a new...

01:07:53.700 --> 01:07:55.067
Doc?

01:08:00.633 --> 01:08:01.867
Doc?

01:08:03.568 --> 01:08:04.834
Doc?

01:08:05.800 --> 01:08:07.468
Dr. Octav...

01:08:13.700 --> 01:08:15.301
It's so quiet.

01:08:18.767 --> 01:08:22.134
Those voices inside my head...

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:28.501
I'd almost forgotten.

01:08:29.800 --> 01:08:30.967
Otto.

01:08:32.134 --> 01:08:34.201
Yes. Norman.

01:08:40.201 --> 01:08:41.501
It's me.

01:08:43.667 --> 01:08:45.067
Would you look at that.

01:09:05.534 --> 01:09:08.667
I'm grateful, dear boy. Truly.

01:09:08.800 --> 01:09:10.800
Yeah, you're welcome.

01:09:10.934 --> 01:09:12.568
How can I help?

01:09:12.700 --> 01:09:14.800
<i>This is Peter. Leave a message.</i>

01:09:14.934 --> 01:09:17.501
Uh, yeah, Peter, this is Happy.

01:09:17.633 --> 01:09:19.301
I accessed my doorbell camera.

01:09:19.434 --> 01:09:21.568
Who are those guys, huh?
Is that a cyborg?

01:09:21.700 --> 01:09:24.034
You bring a cyborg
with robot legs into my house?

01:09:24.167 --> 01:09:26.733
Was one of the guys made of mud?
What's going on? Call me.

01:09:35.867 --> 01:09:37.900
How does it feel, Norman?

01:09:38.034 --> 01:09:40.501
You're about
to become whole again.

01:09:41.667 --> 01:09:44.201
No more darker half.

01:09:44.334 --> 01:09:45.434
Just you.

01:09:46.367 --> 01:09:47.834
Just me.

01:09:56.834 --> 01:09:58.000
Okay, um...

01:09:59.501 --> 01:10:02.600
It just goes right here. This...

01:10:02.733 --> 01:10:04.234
That should be
drawing power now.

01:10:04.367 --> 01:10:06.234
I'm gonna come back
in a second to check,

01:10:06.367 --> 01:10:08.534
but keep an eye on the lights.
When they're all green,

01:10:08.667 --> 01:10:11.034
it means the electricity
in your body's dissipated.

01:10:11.167 --> 01:10:12.501
Well, not all
of the electricity.

01:10:12.667 --> 01:10:14.867
You need electricity
for your brain to function.

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:16.867
Your nervous system is...

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:20.034
I'm not really sure why I'm
explaining electricity to you.

01:10:20.167 --> 01:10:22.067
- Yeah, can I ask you a question?
- Sure.

01:10:22.201 --> 01:10:24.568
Are these your Legos?

01:10:25.600 --> 01:10:28.067
Uh, I gotta go. I'll be back.

01:10:33.534 --> 01:10:36.900
- Something feels off.
- What do you mean?

01:10:37.034 --> 01:10:39.501
- I don't like this.
- Leave it alone.

01:10:39.633 --> 01:10:43.267
The sooner you guys get through
this, the sooner we go home.

01:10:51.301 --> 01:10:53.534
- Well, where is he?
- Uh, he's inside.

01:10:53.667 --> 01:10:55.267
And yet here we are, outside.

01:10:55.401 --> 01:10:57.367
Did you not hear me say,
"Don't lose him?"

01:10:57.501 --> 01:10:59.501
I want incriminating footage
of Spider-Man.

01:10:59.633 --> 01:11:01.401
I called Damage Control.
They're on their way.

01:11:01.534 --> 01:11:03.101
And so it begins.

01:11:03.234 --> 01:11:05.101
...place is about
to be swarming with cops.

01:11:24.167 --> 01:11:25.501
Peter?

01:11:26.934 --> 01:11:28.167
What's wrong?

01:11:29.167 --> 01:11:31.034
I don't know.

01:11:31.167 --> 01:11:32.234
May?

01:11:37.834 --> 01:11:39.334
What is it, Peter?

01:11:46.401 --> 01:11:47.934
What's happening?

01:11:54.667 --> 01:11:56.867
Why are you
looking at me like that?

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:16.700
That's some neat trick,
that sense of yours.

01:12:16.834 --> 01:12:20.967
- Norman?
- Norman's on sabbatical, honey.

01:12:21.101 --> 01:12:23.367
- The hell?
- The Goblin.

01:12:24.600 --> 01:12:26.501
"No more darker half"?

01:12:26.633 --> 01:12:30.034
Did you really think
that I'd let that happen?

01:12:30.167 --> 01:12:33.568
That I'd let you take away my
power just because you're blind

01:12:33.700 --> 01:12:36.234
to what true power
can bring you?

01:12:36.367 --> 01:12:37.900
- You don't know me.
- Don't I?

01:12:41.667 --> 01:12:47.201
I saw how she trapped you,
fighting her holy moral mission.

01:12:49.867 --> 01:12:52.000
We don't need you to save us.

01:12:52.134 --> 01:12:54.234
We don't need to be fixed.

01:12:57.700 --> 01:13:00.434
These are not curses.

01:13:00.568 --> 01:13:02.733
They're gifts.

01:13:04.034 --> 01:13:06.000
- Norman, no.
- Quiet, lapdog.

01:13:06.134 --> 01:13:08.000
You don't know
what you're talking about.

01:13:08.134 --> 01:13:13.067
I've watched you from deep
behind Norman's cowardly eyes.

01:13:13.201 --> 01:13:18.534
Struggling to have
everything you want

01:13:18.667 --> 01:13:22.167
while the world tries
to make you choose.

01:13:24.367 --> 01:13:27.900
Gods don't have to choose.

01:13:29.767 --> 01:13:31.167
We take.

01:13:31.301 --> 01:13:32.733
May, run.

01:13:56.000 --> 01:13:57.867
Oh, my God.

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:01.201
- What have you done?
- I liked you better before.

01:14:10.534 --> 01:14:14.101
Up here. He's up there.
It's the guy from the bridge.

01:14:36.434 --> 01:14:37.568
Did you see that?

01:15:04.067 --> 01:15:05.767
No, you don't!

01:15:14.534 --> 01:15:16.934
Strong enough to have it all.

01:15:20.234 --> 01:15:22.201
Too weak to take it!

01:15:57.201 --> 01:15:58.568
Now I got you.

01:16:00.800 --> 01:16:03.034
I told you
there'd be consequences.

01:16:21.234 --> 01:16:25.101
Your weakness, Peter,
is morality.

01:16:25.234 --> 01:16:29.201
It's choking you.
Can't you feel it?

01:16:37.468 --> 01:16:38.800
It didn't work.

01:16:40.167 --> 01:16:41.733
Norman was right.

01:16:41.867 --> 01:16:45.667
He got it from you,
that pathetic sickness.

01:16:50.301 --> 01:16:52.700
You tried to fix me.

01:16:52.834 --> 01:16:56.468
- May, go.
- Now I'm gonna fix you.

01:17:00.067 --> 01:17:01.434
May, run, please.

01:17:04.568 --> 01:17:06.434
May!

01:17:12.667 --> 01:17:14.767
Peter, Peter, Peter.

01:17:14.900 --> 01:17:18.401
No good deed goes unpunished.

01:17:18.534 --> 01:17:20.767
You can thank me later.

01:17:26.633 --> 01:17:27.967
No!

01:17:57.667 --> 01:17:58.534
- May?
- Peter.

01:17:58.667 --> 01:18:00.434
May, May, I'm here.

01:18:00.568 --> 01:18:02.501
Oh!

01:18:03.967 --> 01:18:05.334
- May.
- Oh!

01:18:05.468 --> 01:18:07.334
May, I'm here.

01:18:07.468 --> 01:18:09.067
- Are you okay?
- Uh-huh, uh-huh.

01:18:09.201 --> 01:18:10.401
What happened?

01:18:13.534 --> 01:18:14.568
Okay... Oh!

01:18:16.201 --> 01:18:18.167
It's okay. We're okay, right?

01:18:18.301 --> 01:18:19.934
Yeah. Knocked on my ass.

01:18:20.067 --> 01:18:21.167
- Yeah, me too.
- That's all.

01:18:23.667 --> 01:18:25.000
I think I broke my ribs.

01:18:30.301 --> 01:18:32.401
- This is all my fault, May.
- No.

01:18:32.534 --> 01:18:34.434
I should have let Strange
send them back.

01:18:34.568 --> 01:18:36.434
You did the right thing.

01:18:36.568 --> 01:18:38.334
They would have been killed.

01:18:38.468 --> 01:18:40.234
You did the right thing.

01:18:40.367 --> 01:18:42.867
It's not my responsibility, May.

01:18:44.700 --> 01:18:47.234
Oh. What Norman said?

01:18:48.568 --> 01:18:50.501
My moral mission? No.

01:18:50.633 --> 01:18:52.900
- No, May...
- Peter, you listen to me.

01:18:54.067 --> 01:18:55.167
You have a gift.

01:18:56.667 --> 01:18:58.767
You have power.

01:18:58.900 --> 01:19:00.267
And with great power,

01:19:00.401 --> 01:19:04.468
there must also come
great responsibility, mm?

01:19:09.134 --> 01:19:10.568
Yeah, I know.

01:19:10.700 --> 01:19:12.367
Let's get the... out of here.

01:19:12.501 --> 01:19:14.167
Okay, let's go.

01:19:14.301 --> 01:19:16.967
Let me just catch my...

01:19:32.334 --> 01:19:34.534
- What happened? Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

01:19:34.667 --> 01:19:36.501
Yeah, you're okay.
What happened?

01:19:38.267 --> 01:19:40.334
Just have to...

01:19:40.468 --> 01:19:42.633
- catch my breath.
- Okay, well, catch your breath.

01:19:42.767 --> 01:19:44.667
I'm right here.
We're gonna take our time.

01:19:44.800 --> 01:19:46.034
You catch your breath.

01:19:46.167 --> 01:19:48.534
Then we'll take you
to a doctor, okay?

01:20:06.167 --> 01:20:08.101
Are you okay?

01:20:08.234 --> 01:20:11.067
Somebody help! I need
an ambulance, please! Somebody?

01:20:11.201 --> 01:20:14.101
- What happened?
- Nothing happened.

01:20:14.234 --> 01:20:15.934
You're okay, you're okay.

01:20:17.633 --> 01:20:20.034
Let me just...
Let me catch my breath.

01:20:20.167 --> 01:20:22.501
I'm right here. I'm right here.

01:20:22.633 --> 01:20:24.234
I'm right here.

01:20:30.667 --> 01:20:32.067
You're okay.

01:20:33.334 --> 01:20:34.867
It's just me and you.

01:20:44.633 --> 01:20:45.867
May?

01:20:52.067 --> 01:20:53.401
May?

01:20:59.334 --> 01:21:01.267
Will you look at me,
May, please?

01:21:09.534 --> 01:21:10.700
May.

01:21:11.633 --> 01:21:12.834
May.

01:21:14.034 --> 01:21:15.633
What are you doing, May?

01:21:15.767 --> 01:21:18.468
Please, will you just wake up
and talk to me? Please?

01:21:41.301 --> 01:21:43.067
Get out of the car now! Move!

01:21:49.534 --> 01:21:51.301
Get off, get off, get off me.

01:21:53.568 --> 01:21:56.201
- Peter! Run!
- It's just me and you, okay?

01:21:56.334 --> 01:21:58.167
It's just me and you, okay?

01:21:58.301 --> 01:22:01.234
Oh, May, I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

01:22:01.367 --> 01:22:03.401
I'm so, so, so sorry.
I love you.

01:22:03.534 --> 01:22:06.034
All right, Parker!
Come out with your hands up!

01:22:06.167 --> 01:22:08.667
Come out right
now, or we will open fire!

01:22:08.800 --> 01:22:10.600
Run!

01:22:13.633 --> 01:22:16.401
All right, let's go.
Let's go! Move in!

01:22:33.967 --> 01:22:35.534
<i>Tragedy.</i>

01:22:38.867 --> 01:22:41.267
<i>What else can I call it?</i>

01:22:41.401 --> 01:22:43.367
<i>What more need be said?</i>

01:22:43.501 --> 01:22:47.568
<i>The damage, the destruction.</i>

01:22:47.700 --> 01:22:50.267
<i>You saw it with your own eyes.</i>

01:22:50.401 --> 01:22:53.267
<i>When will people wake up
and realize</i>

01:22:53.401 --> 01:22:55.934
<i>that everywhere
Spider-Man goes,</i>

01:22:56.067 --> 01:22:59.633
<i>chaos and calamity ensue?</i>

01:22:59.767 --> 01:23:04.834
<i>Everything Spider-Man touches
comes to ruin.</i>

01:23:04.967 --> 01:23:07.501
<i>And we, the innocents,</i>

01:23:07.633 --> 01:23:10.067
<i>are left to pick up the pieces.</i>

01:23:12.101 --> 01:23:14.167
<i>J. Jonah Jameson reporting.</i>

01:23:14.301 --> 01:23:17.568
<i>Good night,
and God help us all.</i>

01:23:37.000 --> 01:23:40.134
<i>We are told that multiple
people have been injured,</i>

01:23:40.267 --> 01:23:44.700
<i>and we can confirm at least
one person has been killed...</i>

01:23:44.834 --> 01:23:46.334
Still nothing?

01:23:47.534 --> 01:23:48.967
No.

01:24:04.501 --> 01:24:06.000
I'm gonna press it.

01:24:07.468 --> 01:24:10.167
- What? No, he...
- I know he told me to wait...

01:24:11.501 --> 01:24:13.667
- but I'm gonna do it.
- I just wish...

01:24:13.800 --> 01:24:15.501
I just wish we could see him.

01:24:20.700 --> 01:24:22.667
- Ned?
- Yeah?

01:24:22.800 --> 01:24:24.834
- Do that again.
- Yeah.

01:24:26.733 --> 01:24:28.900
I just wish we could see him.

01:24:30.867 --> 01:24:33.367
Oh. Okay.

01:24:33.501 --> 01:24:35.867
I just wish we could see Peter.

01:24:39.234 --> 01:24:42.000
Whoa.

01:24:42.134 --> 01:24:45.067
<i>Lola,</i> you're right. I am magic.

01:24:45.201 --> 01:24:46.934
Is that him?

01:24:47.067 --> 01:24:49.401
- Yeah, yeah, it has to be.
- Peter. Peter!

01:24:49.534 --> 01:24:51.067
- Hey, Peter!
- Peter!

01:24:51.201 --> 01:24:52.667
Yeah.

01:24:56.967 --> 01:24:57.867
Whoa!

01:25:00.000 --> 01:25:01.501
Hi. Hi.

01:25:01.633 --> 01:25:04.667
No, no, no, it's okay.
It's okay. I'm a nice guy.

01:25:07.401 --> 01:25:08.834
Okay.

01:25:11.334 --> 01:25:13.867
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm Peter Parker.

01:25:14.000 --> 01:25:18.067
- That's not possible.
- I am Spider-Man, in my world.

01:25:18.201 --> 01:25:21.367
But then yesterday, I was...

01:25:23.034 --> 01:25:24.900
I was just here.

01:25:26.434 --> 01:25:27.700
Wow.

01:25:29.301 --> 01:25:33.867
String theory,
multi-dimensional reality...

01:25:34.000 --> 01:25:36.201
and matter displacement.

01:25:36.334 --> 01:25:38.167
- All real?
- Yeah.

01:25:38.301 --> 01:25:39.900
I knew it.

01:25:41.201 --> 01:25:43.501
This has to be
because of the spell.

01:25:43.633 --> 01:25:45.334
The spell? Like magic spell?

01:25:45.468 --> 01:25:47.301
- There's no spell. No.
- No spell.

01:25:47.434 --> 01:25:49.134
- Magic's real here too?
- I mean...

01:25:49.267 --> 01:25:51.034
- Shut up, Ned.
- No, it's not <i>real.</i>

01:25:51.167 --> 01:25:54.234
- Shut up. Stop talking.
- There's magicians, but no...

01:25:54.367 --> 01:25:56.700
Stop. Stop.

01:25:56.834 --> 01:25:58.134
- Prove it.
- Prove what?

01:25:58.267 --> 01:26:00.234
- That you're Peter Parker.
- I don't carry

01:26:00.367 --> 01:26:01.900
an ID with me, you know?

01:26:02.034 --> 01:26:04.800
Kind of defeats the whole
anonymous superhero thing.

01:26:06.834 --> 01:26:08.900
- Why'd you do that?
- To see if you have the tingle.

01:26:09.034 --> 01:26:10.967
I have the tingle thing,
just not for bread.

01:26:11.101 --> 01:26:13.034
Can you not
throw the bread again?

01:26:13.167 --> 01:26:15.867
You're a deeply
mistrusting person...

01:26:17.134 --> 01:26:18.733
and I respect it.

01:26:23.700 --> 01:26:24.568
Crawl around.

01:26:24.700 --> 01:26:26.568
- Crawl around?
- Yes.

01:26:26.700 --> 01:26:28.267
- No.
- Yes, crawl around.

01:26:28.401 --> 01:26:29.934
- Why do I need to?
- This is not enough.

01:26:30.067 --> 01:26:31.367
- This is plenty.
- No, it's not.

01:26:31.501 --> 01:26:33.101
- Yes, it is. It is.
- No, it's not. Nuh-uh.

01:26:33.234 --> 01:26:35.867
- How do I stick to the ceiling?
- Do it.

01:26:37.167 --> 01:26:38.434
Ned.

01:26:44.067 --> 01:26:45.834
My <i>lola's</i> asking
if you could just

01:26:45.967 --> 01:26:47.434
get the cobweb there.

01:26:47.568 --> 01:26:49.834
- Since you're, like, up there.
- Yeah.

01:26:57.468 --> 01:26:59.101
Thank you.

01:27:03.201 --> 01:27:04.534
We goo...?

01:27:04.667 --> 01:27:07.101
- We good?
- For now.

01:27:07.234 --> 01:27:10.167
So I opened the wrong portal
to the wrong Peter Parker.

01:27:10.301 --> 01:27:12.534
I guess you keep doing it
until we find the real one.

01:27:12.667 --> 01:27:15.101
- Ouch.
- No offense.

01:27:15.234 --> 01:27:17.067
- Okay.
- Okay. You got it.

01:27:19.134 --> 01:27:20.468
Find Peter Parker.

01:27:20.600 --> 01:27:22.568
- What's the thing on his hand?
- Shh.

01:27:22.700 --> 01:27:25.000
Find Peter Parker.

01:27:26.733 --> 01:27:28.700
Find Peter Parker!

01:27:37.633 --> 01:27:39.834
Great, it's just
some random guy.

01:27:39.967 --> 01:27:41.167
Hello.

01:27:41.301 --> 01:27:42.633
Um, I hope it's okay,

01:27:42.767 --> 01:27:44.733
I just came through this, uh...

01:27:44.867 --> 01:27:46.867
Oh. It just closed.

01:27:48.334 --> 01:27:49.534
You're Peter?

01:27:49.667 --> 01:27:52.700
Yeah. Peter Parker.

01:27:54.767 --> 01:27:56.501
I... I've seen you two...

01:27:58.867 --> 01:28:00.234
Hi. Heh.

01:28:03.967 --> 01:28:06.667
Wait. He's...
He's not <i>your</i> friend.

01:28:19.267 --> 01:28:22.334
Huh.

01:28:22.468 --> 01:28:25.534
Wait. So you're Spider-Man too?
Why didn't you just say that?

01:28:25.667 --> 01:28:28.067
I generally don't
go around advertising it.

01:28:28.201 --> 01:28:30.867
Kind of defeats the whole
anonymous superhero thing.

01:28:31.000 --> 01:28:32.700
- I said that.
- That's what he just said.

01:28:44.568 --> 01:28:48.067
My <i>lola's</i> asking if you could
clean up the webs you just shot.

01:28:48.201 --> 01:28:49.867
- Oh, sorry, <i>Lola.</i>
- Yes, of course.

01:28:50.000 --> 01:28:52.234
- I'm going to bed.
- Night, <i>Lola.</i>

01:28:52.367 --> 01:28:54.167
Good night, Ned's <i>lola.</i>

01:28:54.301 --> 01:28:57.067
Uh,
this might seem kind of weird,

01:28:57.201 --> 01:28:59.034
but I've been trying
to find your friend

01:28:59.167 --> 01:29:01.201
ever since I got here.

01:29:01.334 --> 01:29:03.434
I just have this sense that...

01:29:05.201 --> 01:29:06.434
That he needs my help.

01:29:06.568 --> 01:29:08.101
Our help.

01:29:09.534 --> 01:29:10.568
He does.

01:29:10.700 --> 01:29:12.367
We don't know where he is.

01:29:12.501 --> 01:29:17.900
And, um, honestly, right now
we're all he really has left.

01:29:18.034 --> 01:29:23.034
Well, uh, is there someplace
that he might go

01:29:23.167 --> 01:29:25.568
that has meaning to him?

01:29:26.800 --> 01:29:30.234
Like a place
where he would go to just...?

01:29:30.367 --> 01:29:32.301
Get away from everything?

01:29:34.967 --> 01:29:38.167
For me, it was the top
of the Chrysler Building.

01:29:38.301 --> 01:29:40.167
Empire State.

01:29:40.301 --> 01:29:43.334
- It's a better view.
- That is a sweet view.

01:29:45.600 --> 01:29:47.401
Yes.

01:29:47.534 --> 01:29:50.967
Yeah. I... I think I know
exactly where that would be.

01:30:26.667 --> 01:30:28.000
I'm sorry.

01:30:35.167 --> 01:30:36.667
Peter, there's...

01:30:37.834 --> 01:30:39.733
There's some people here.

01:30:40.867 --> 01:30:42.700
- What?
- Um...

01:30:51.367 --> 01:30:53.201
Hey, wait, wait! Whoa!

01:30:53.334 --> 01:30:54.401
What...?

01:30:57.234 --> 01:30:58.267
Sorry...

01:31:00.134 --> 01:31:01.167
about May.

01:31:04.800 --> 01:31:07.101
Yeah. Sorry.

01:31:08.867 --> 01:31:10.867
I got some understanding
of what it is you're...

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:14.234
No, please don't tell me that
you know what I'm going through.

01:31:14.367 --> 01:31:16.667
- Okay.
- She's gone.

01:31:19.167 --> 01:31:20.568
And it's all my fault.

01:31:24.733 --> 01:31:26.367
She died for nothing.

01:31:29.934 --> 01:31:32.401
So I'm gonna do what I should
have done in the first place.

01:31:32.534 --> 01:31:34.167
- Peter...
- Please don't.

01:31:35.201 --> 01:31:36.301
You don't belong here.

01:31:36.434 --> 01:31:37.367
Either of you.

01:31:37.501 --> 01:31:39.900
So I'm sending you home.

01:31:40.034 --> 01:31:43.000
Those other guys
are from your worlds, right?

01:31:43.134 --> 01:31:44.568
So you deal with it.

01:31:44.700 --> 01:31:47.334
If they die, if you kill them...

01:31:47.468 --> 01:31:48.501
that's on you.

01:31:49.633 --> 01:31:51.334
It's not my problem.

01:31:51.468 --> 01:31:52.900
I don't care anymore.

01:31:54.101 --> 01:31:55.367
I'm done.

01:31:59.967 --> 01:32:02.633
I'm really sorry
that I dragged you into this.

01:32:05.934 --> 01:32:07.900
But you have to go home now.

01:32:10.134 --> 01:32:11.367
Good luck.

01:32:16.667 --> 01:32:18.667
My Uncle Ben was killed.

01:32:20.101 --> 01:32:21.468
It was my fault.

01:32:22.700 --> 01:32:24.134
I lost...

01:32:26.800 --> 01:32:28.834
I lost Gwen, my, um...

01:32:30.134 --> 01:32:31.900
She was my MJ.

01:32:34.000 --> 01:32:35.534
I couldn't save her.

01:32:37.167 --> 01:32:39.900
I'm never gonna be able
to forgive myself for that.

01:32:42.334 --> 01:32:44.667
But I carried on,
tried to, um...

01:32:44.800 --> 01:32:48.000
Tried to keep going,
tried to keep being the, uh...

01:32:49.468 --> 01:32:51.267
The friendly neighborhood
Spider-Man

01:32:51.401 --> 01:32:54.267
'cause I know that's what
she would've wanted.

01:32:54.401 --> 01:32:58.067
But at some point, I just...
I stopped pulling my punches.

01:33:01.667 --> 01:33:03.167
I got rageful.

01:33:05.301 --> 01:33:06.667
I got bitter.

01:33:08.000 --> 01:33:09.534
I just don't want you

01:33:09.667 --> 01:33:12.367
to end up like... Like me.

01:33:13.834 --> 01:33:16.767
The night Ben died...

01:33:16.900 --> 01:33:19.600
I hunted down the man
who I thought did it.

01:33:21.401 --> 01:33:23.167
I wanted him dead.

01:33:25.633 --> 01:33:27.167
I got what I wanted.

01:33:29.534 --> 01:33:31.568
It didn't make it better.

01:33:35.101 --> 01:33:37.568
It took me a long time...

01:33:39.334 --> 01:33:41.733
to learn to get through
that darkness.

01:33:44.334 --> 01:33:46.034
I wanna kill him.

01:33:48.367 --> 01:33:50.334
I wanna tear him apart.

01:33:53.934 --> 01:33:56.401
I can still hear
her voice in my head.

01:34:01.267 --> 01:34:02.900
Even after she was hurt,

01:34:03.034 --> 01:34:05.733
she said to me
that we did the right thing.

01:34:14.434 --> 01:34:16.201
She told me
that with great power...

01:34:18.301 --> 01:34:20.134
Comes great responsibility.

01:34:25.367 --> 01:34:26.867
Wait, what?
How do you know that?

01:34:27.000 --> 01:34:28.501
Uncle Ben said it.

01:34:28.633 --> 01:34:30.167
The day he died.

01:34:34.800 --> 01:34:37.167
Maybe she didn't die
for nothing, Peter.

01:34:46.900 --> 01:34:52.568
Okay, so, uh, Connors,
Marko, Dillon and, um...

01:34:52.700 --> 01:34:55.501
I think that I can repair the
devices for Dillon and Marko,

01:34:55.633 --> 01:34:57.367
but the others...

01:34:57.501 --> 01:35:00.733
Oh, I got Connors. I've cured
him once, so no big deal.

01:35:02.367 --> 01:35:05.000
- What? It's no big deal.
- Great.

01:35:05.134 --> 01:35:06.733
Yeah, that's great.

01:35:09.000 --> 01:35:12.834
I think I can make
an anti-serum for Dr. Osborn.

01:35:12.967 --> 01:35:14.867
Been thinking about it
a long time.

01:35:17.867 --> 01:35:20.934
Gotta cure all of them. Right?

01:35:21.967 --> 01:35:23.101
Right.

01:35:24.534 --> 01:35:26.201
That's what we do.

01:35:34.234 --> 01:35:35.667
What?

01:35:35.800 --> 01:35:37.234
Just three yous.

01:35:52.800 --> 01:35:53.834
Um...

01:35:55.367 --> 01:35:58.967
So do you have
a best friend too?

01:36:00.834 --> 01:36:02.134
I did.

01:36:03.834 --> 01:36:05.234
You did?

01:36:06.667 --> 01:36:08.468
He died in my arms...

01:36:10.034 --> 01:36:12.034
after he tried to kill me.

01:36:13.667 --> 01:36:15.633
It was heartbreaking.

01:36:17.334 --> 01:36:18.700
Dude.

01:36:25.367 --> 01:36:27.800
- Hey.
- Will you run a diagnostic?

01:36:27.934 --> 01:36:29.134
Yeah.

01:36:38.367 --> 01:36:40.501
Hey, you okay?

01:36:40.633 --> 01:36:42.568
Uh, yeah, I'm fine.
Are you okay?

01:36:42.700 --> 01:36:44.000
Mm-hm.

01:36:46.633 --> 01:36:49.334
You don't deserve this.

01:36:49.468 --> 01:36:53.367
- I've ruined your life.
- No. No, no, no.

01:36:53.501 --> 01:36:55.568
Look at me. I'm here.

01:36:56.967 --> 01:36:58.434
Not going anywhere.

01:36:59.733 --> 01:37:01.067
We're gonna get through this.

01:37:01.201 --> 01:37:03.834
And we're gonna get
through it together.

01:37:03.967 --> 01:37:05.234
Okay?

01:37:06.334 --> 01:37:09.034
Okay.

01:37:13.367 --> 01:37:14.700
Thank you.

01:37:25.834 --> 01:37:27.867
You have someone?

01:37:28.000 --> 01:37:29.568
No.

01:37:29.700 --> 01:37:34.600
Ah, I got no time for
Peter Parker stuff, you know?

01:37:34.733 --> 01:37:36.201
Hm.

01:37:36.334 --> 01:37:38.834
- Do you?
- Uh...

01:37:38.967 --> 01:37:43.067
- that's a little complicated.
- Oh, I understand.

01:37:43.201 --> 01:37:45.667
I guess it's just not
in the cards for guys like us.

01:37:45.800 --> 01:37:48.334
Well, I wouldn't give up.

01:37:48.468 --> 01:37:51.334
Took a while
but we made it work.

01:37:51.468 --> 01:37:53.034
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:37:53.167 --> 01:37:54.633
Me and...

01:37:54.767 --> 01:37:55.967
MJ.

01:37:57.334 --> 01:37:59.234
My MJ. Uh...

01:38:00.367 --> 01:38:02.800
It gets confusing here.

01:38:02.934 --> 01:38:04.067
Yeah.

01:38:04.201 --> 01:38:06.167
- Peter!
- Yeah?

01:38:06.301 --> 01:38:09.633
- Oh, sorry, did you mean...?
- "Peter" Peter.

01:38:09.767 --> 01:38:11.534
- We're all called Peter.
- We're all Peter.

01:38:11.667 --> 01:38:14.667
- Peter Parker?
- Again, we're all Peter Parker.

01:38:14.800 --> 01:38:17.401
- The computer.
- Oh!

01:38:17.534 --> 01:38:19.134
- Oh, I'm ready.
- Yeah. Me too.

01:38:19.267 --> 01:38:21.568
Okay, so now, all we gotta do

01:38:21.700 --> 01:38:24.201
is lure these guys
someplace, right?

01:38:24.334 --> 01:38:27.800
Try to cure them
while they try to kill us,

01:38:27.934 --> 01:38:29.401
and then send them home.

01:38:29.534 --> 01:38:32.134
- Using a magic box.
- Well, that's the plan.

01:38:32.267 --> 01:38:35.367
Are you gonna go into battle
dressed as a cool youth pastor,

01:38:35.501 --> 01:38:37.167
or do you got your suit?

01:38:38.367 --> 01:38:40.501
- Good.
- Here's your web cartridges.

01:38:40.633 --> 01:38:43.067
- Oh, thanks, man.
- What's that for?

01:38:43.201 --> 01:38:46.501
Uh, it's my web fluid.
It's for my web shooters. Why?

01:38:46.633 --> 01:38:48.101
Whoa!

01:38:49.334 --> 01:38:50.334
That came out of you.

01:38:50.468 --> 01:38:52.367
Yeah. You can't do that, huh?

01:38:52.501 --> 01:38:54.700
- No.
- How on earth does that...?

01:38:54.834 --> 01:38:57.534
We're getting sidetracked. This
is where we'll do this, okay?

01:38:57.667 --> 01:39:00.067
It's isolated,
so no one should get hurt.

01:39:00.201 --> 01:39:02.568
We draw them there with the box.
It's the thing they want.

01:39:02.700 --> 01:39:04.767
All we have to do
is figure out how to get there.

01:39:04.900 --> 01:39:06.267
- We could portal there.
- What?

01:39:06.401 --> 01:39:08.767
- I'm magic now.
- Yeah, he's right. He can.

01:39:08.900 --> 01:39:10.934
- Yeah, we saw.
- Yeah, he is.

01:39:11.067 --> 01:39:12.900
- Wait, really?
- I got Doctor Strange magic.

01:39:13.034 --> 01:39:14.867
- No way.
- Yeah.

01:39:15.000 --> 01:39:17.267
I promise,
I won't turn into a supervillain

01:39:17.401 --> 01:39:18.934
and try to kill you.

01:39:20.700 --> 01:39:22.600
Okay.

01:39:22.733 --> 01:39:24.367
Thank you.

01:39:28.834 --> 01:39:31.101
Um, all right,
here goes nothing.

01:39:31.234 --> 01:39:33.234
What's that thing
you always say?

01:39:33.367 --> 01:39:36.934
- Expect disappointment and...
- No, no, no.

01:39:37.067 --> 01:39:38.733
We're gonna kick some ass.

01:39:38.867 --> 01:39:40.401
Okay.

01:39:40.534 --> 01:39:43.034
Cure. Cure some ass.

01:39:43.167 --> 01:39:44.934
Cure that ass.

01:39:47.167 --> 01:39:48.800
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

01:39:48.934 --> 01:39:50.900
<i>the</i> Bugle <i>tip line</i>
<i>has just received a call</i>

01:39:51.034 --> 01:39:53.967
<i>from none other than the
fugitive known as Spider-Man,</i>

01:39:54.101 --> 01:39:57.167
<i>fresh from his rampage
in Queens.</i>

01:39:57.301 --> 01:39:58.834
<i>So, Peter Parker,</i>

01:39:58.967 --> 01:40:01.367
<i>what pernicious propaganda
are you peddling?</i>

01:40:01.501 --> 01:40:03.134
- <i>Just the truth.</i>
- <i>Oh, sure.</i>

01:40:03.267 --> 01:40:05.733
<i>The truth is...</i>

01:40:05.867 --> 01:40:08.067
<i>that this is all my fault.</i>

01:40:08.201 --> 01:40:10.733
<i>I accidentally brought
those dangerous people here.</i>

01:40:10.867 --> 01:40:12.468
Well, he admits it.

01:40:12.600 --> 01:40:14.568
<i>And if those people
are watching...</i>

01:40:16.167 --> 01:40:19.234
<i>just know that I really did
try to help you.</i>

01:40:19.367 --> 01:40:22.000
<i>I mean,
I could have killed you...</i>

01:40:22.134 --> 01:40:24.733
<i>at any given moment,
but I didn't.</i>

01:40:26.434 --> 01:40:27.733
<i>My Aunt May taught me</i>

01:40:27.867 --> 01:40:29.667
<i>that everyone deserves
a second chance.</i>

01:40:29.800 --> 01:40:30.700
<i>That's why I'm here.</i>

01:40:30.834 --> 01:40:32.733
And where is "here," exactly?

01:40:34.633 --> 01:40:36.733
A place that represents
second chances.

01:40:39.600 --> 01:40:42.301
<i>The Statue of Liberty?
Good God, folks.</i>

01:40:42.434 --> 01:40:45.633
<i>He's about to destroy
another national landmark.</i>

01:40:45.767 --> 01:40:47.367
World, if you're watching...

01:40:47.501 --> 01:40:50.067
<i>Believe me,
the world is watching.</i>

01:40:50.201 --> 01:40:51.700
...wish me luck.

01:40:53.201 --> 01:40:55.434
Your friendly neighborhood
Spider-Man could use some.

01:41:01.900 --> 01:41:04.000
Okay, guys,
it could be any minute now.

01:41:04.134 --> 01:41:06.401
Yep, almost done.

01:41:11.234 --> 01:41:15.767
You know, Max was like
the sweetest guy ever

01:41:15.900 --> 01:41:20.367
before he fell into...
a pool of electric eels.

01:41:20.501 --> 01:41:22.167
That'll do it.

01:41:23.501 --> 01:41:25.568
Mm. Oh, there it goes.

01:41:26.834 --> 01:41:28.700
Heh, you okay?

01:41:28.834 --> 01:41:30.600
Oh, it's my back.

01:41:30.733 --> 01:41:34.000
It's kind of stiff
from all the swinging, I guess.

01:41:34.134 --> 01:41:36.000
Yeah. No, I got
a middle back thing too.

01:41:36.134 --> 01:41:39.501
- Really?
- Yeah. You want me to crack it?

01:41:39.633 --> 01:41:40.934
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

01:41:41.067 --> 01:41:42.733
- Yeah, that'd be great.
- All right.

01:41:44.134 --> 01:41:45.334
- You ready?
- Yeah.

01:41:48.568 --> 01:41:50.767
Yep. That's good.

01:41:50.900 --> 01:41:54.067
- How is it?
- Wow.

01:41:54.201 --> 01:41:56.568
- That's good. That's better.
- Right? Yeah.

01:41:56.700 --> 01:41:57.733
Wow.

01:42:01.000 --> 01:42:03.900
This is so cool.
I always wanted brothers.

01:42:05.468 --> 01:42:08.468
So you, like, make your own
web fluid in your body?

01:42:08.600 --> 01:42:10.234
I'd rather not talk about this.

01:42:10.367 --> 01:42:12.301
- I don't mean to...
- But are you teasing me?

01:42:12.434 --> 01:42:13.800
No, no.
He's not teasing you.

01:42:13.934 --> 01:42:16.201
It's just that we can't do that,

01:42:16.334 --> 01:42:19.733
so we're curious as to how your
web situation works, that's all.

01:42:19.867 --> 01:42:22.534
If it's personal, I don't wanna
pry, but I think it's cool.

01:42:22.667 --> 01:42:25.700
I... I wish I could tell you,
but it's, like, I don't do it.

01:42:25.834 --> 01:42:28.167
Like I don't...
Like I don't <i>do</i> breathing.

01:42:28.301 --> 01:42:30.167
- Like, breathing just happens.
- Whoa.

01:42:30.301 --> 01:42:32.034
Does it just come out
of your wrists,

01:42:32.167 --> 01:42:34.568
or does it come out
of anywhere else?

01:42:34.700 --> 01:42:36.867
Only... Only the wrists.

01:42:37.000 --> 01:42:39.167
Never had a block?
I run out of webs all the time.

01:42:39.301 --> 01:42:41.733
- I have to make my own in a lab.
- Right. That's...

01:42:41.867 --> 01:42:44.000
It's a hassle compared
to what you got.

01:42:44.134 --> 01:42:45.534
Sounds like a hassle.
But I did.

01:42:45.667 --> 01:42:46.900
You said that, I was like,

01:42:47.034 --> 01:42:49.633
- "Oh, I had a web block."
- Whoa. Why?

01:42:49.767 --> 01:42:51.401
Existential crisis stuff.

01:42:51.534 --> 01:42:52.967
Yeah.
Don't get me started on that.

01:42:53.101 --> 01:42:56.167
Hey. What are, like,
some of the craziest villains

01:42:56.301 --> 01:42:58.568
- that you guys have fought?
- Seems you've met some of them.

01:42:58.700 --> 01:43:00.267
Heh-heh, that's a good question.

01:43:00.401 --> 01:43:05.700
Yeah, I fought an alien
made out of black goo once.

01:43:05.834 --> 01:43:07.900
Oh, no way.
I fought an alien too.

01:43:08.034 --> 01:43:09.700
- On Earth and in space.
- Oh.

01:43:09.834 --> 01:43:11.568
- He was purple.
- I wanna fight an alien.

01:43:11.700 --> 01:43:16.234
I'm still, like, that you fought
an alien in space.

01:43:16.367 --> 01:43:19.034
I'm lame compared...
I fought a Russian guy

01:43:19.167 --> 01:43:20.534
in a rhinoceros machine.

01:43:20.667 --> 01:43:23.334
Can we rewind it back
to the "I'm lame" part?

01:43:23.468 --> 01:43:25.767
- 'Cause you are not.
- Thanks. I appreciate that.

01:43:25.900 --> 01:43:28.101
- I'm not saying I am...
- But it's just the self-talk.

01:43:28.234 --> 01:43:30.067
- Maybe we should...
- Listen, I...

01:43:30.201 --> 01:43:31.667
'Cause you're amazing.

01:43:31.800 --> 01:43:33.667
Just to take it in for a minute.

01:43:33.800 --> 01:43:36.234
- Yeah, I can take it in.
- You... You are amazing.

01:43:36.367 --> 01:43:38.034
- I can. Thank you.
- You are amazing.

01:43:38.167 --> 01:43:39.867
- Will you say it?
- I needed to hear that.

01:43:40.000 --> 01:43:41.534
Thank you.

01:43:41.667 --> 01:43:44.034
All right, guys, focus up.
You feel that?

01:43:44.167 --> 01:43:45.434
Yeah.

01:43:52.568 --> 01:43:54.501
What's up, Peter?

01:43:56.800 --> 01:43:59.201
How you like the new-new?

01:43:59.334 --> 01:44:03.167
Look, you give it to me,
I'm gonna destroy it.

01:44:04.667 --> 01:44:06.501
But I'll let you live.

01:44:06.633 --> 01:44:09.000
Don't make me a murderer, Peter.

01:44:11.034 --> 01:44:13.067
Okay, guys, here he comes.

01:44:19.501 --> 01:44:22.334
Hey, Max, I missed you, man. Ho!

01:44:24.934 --> 01:44:27.367
All right, MJ, heads up!

01:44:27.501 --> 01:44:29.633
Got it! Close it.

01:44:31.767 --> 01:44:33.534
Uh, Ned, it's not closing.

01:44:33.667 --> 01:44:34.800
Yeah, I know.

01:44:34.934 --> 01:44:36.534
- Why isn't it closing?
- I don't know.

01:44:36.667 --> 01:44:39.700
- Did you close it before? No?
- I mean, I've opened some.

01:44:48.534 --> 01:44:50.900
Max, Max, Max.
Can we talk for a second?

01:44:51.034 --> 01:44:53.700
- Just you and me, just talk?
- Look who showed up.

01:44:53.834 --> 01:44:55.967
- My old friend Spider-Man.
- I'm trying to save you.

01:44:56.101 --> 01:44:58.267
- That's all I've ever wanted.
- You're not trying to save me.

01:44:58.401 --> 01:45:00.667
- I am.
- You ain't even the shit no more.

01:45:00.800 --> 01:45:02.501
- Oh...
- Don't worry about me.

01:45:02.633 --> 01:45:04.667
I'll save myself.

01:45:04.800 --> 01:45:07.401
- Burn up!
- Aah! Whoa!

01:45:07.534 --> 01:45:09.167
Well, I got his attention.
Now what?

01:45:09.301 --> 01:45:10.733
Okay, great.

01:45:10.867 --> 01:45:14.834
Just FYI, lizard guy's here too.

01:45:16.301 --> 01:45:18.534
Guys, comm check. Hello?

01:45:18.667 --> 01:45:20.101
<i>I need Max's cure.</i>

01:45:20.234 --> 01:45:22.334
Yeah. I'm on it.

01:45:22.468 --> 01:45:23.834
<i>I need the Lizard cure.</i>

01:45:23.967 --> 01:45:26.167
Uh, okay, okay.

01:45:31.167 --> 01:45:32.834
Where's the box, Peter?

01:45:32.967 --> 01:45:35.201
- Flint, we could help everyone.
- I don't care!

01:45:47.067 --> 01:45:48.267
Sorry!

01:45:49.501 --> 01:45:50.568
Gross!

01:45:50.700 --> 01:45:52.067
Sad to tell you, Sandman,

01:45:52.201 --> 01:45:53.900
nobody's going home.

01:46:32.267 --> 01:46:34.034
What the hell
is going on out there?

01:46:34.167 --> 01:46:35.867
I keep yelling at you, Peter 2!

01:46:36.000 --> 01:46:39.134
- But I thought you were Peter 2.
- What? I'm not Peter 2.

01:46:39.267 --> 01:46:41.468
Stop arguing, both of you!
Listen to Peter 1.

01:46:41.600 --> 01:46:43.401
We're clearly
not very good at this.

01:46:43.534 --> 01:46:44.633
I know, I know. We suck.

01:46:44.767 --> 01:46:46.468
I don't know
how to work as a team.

01:46:46.600 --> 01:46:49.401
- Me neither.
- I do. I've been in a team, okay?

01:46:49.534 --> 01:46:51.067
I don't wanna brag, but I will.

01:46:51.201 --> 01:46:52.134
I was in the Avengers.

01:46:52.267 --> 01:46:53.534
- The Avengers?
- Yeah.

01:46:53.667 --> 01:46:54.867
- That's great.
- Thank you.

01:46:55.000 --> 01:46:56.867
What is that?

01:46:57.000 --> 01:46:58.967
- You don't have the Avengers?
- Is that a band?

01:46:59.101 --> 01:47:01.534
- Are you in a band?
- No, I'm not in a band.

01:47:01.667 --> 01:47:03.201
The Avengers is
Earth's mightiest...

01:47:03.334 --> 01:47:05.034
- How's this helping?
- It's not important.

01:47:05.167 --> 01:47:06.934
All we gotta do is focus,
trust your tingle

01:47:07.067 --> 01:47:08.434
and coordinate our attacks.

01:47:08.568 --> 01:47:10.000
Yes. Okay.

01:47:10.134 --> 01:47:12.000
- Let's pick one target.
- Right.

01:47:12.134 --> 01:47:13.667
We take them off the board
one at a time.

01:47:13.800 --> 01:47:16.334
- You got it. Peter 1, Peter 2.
- Peter 2.

01:47:16.468 --> 01:47:17.700
- Peter 3.
- Peter 3.

01:47:17.834 --> 01:47:20.434
- Let's do this. Ready?
- Wait, wait, wait!

01:47:20.568 --> 01:47:22.234
I love you guys.

01:47:24.633 --> 01:47:26.000
Thank you.

01:47:27.367 --> 01:47:29.534
- All right, let's do this.
- Let's go.

01:47:35.334 --> 01:47:37.067
Yes!

01:47:58.800 --> 01:48:00.733
Okay, Spider-Mans.

01:48:00.867 --> 01:48:02.834
Sandman's first.

01:48:02.967 --> 01:48:05.034
I'm gonna lead him
inside the statue.

01:48:05.167 --> 01:48:07.667
I'll meet you at the top.

01:48:09.301 --> 01:48:11.067
- Come on!
- Hey!

01:48:14.101 --> 01:48:17.067
- Hey, Dr. Connors.
- Hello, Peter.

